WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:16.308 --> 00:00:19.226
[ Fireworks Exploding ]

3
00:00:23.774 --> 00:00:26.691
Walter.
[ Speaking Portugese ]...

4
00:00:29.530 --> 00:00:31.434
l do.

5
00:00:31.538 --> 00:00:34.616
Florinda.
[ Speaking Portugese ]...

6
00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:38.956
l do.

7
00:00:39.045 --> 00:00:42.147
[ Speaking Portugese
Continues ]...

8
00:00:44.545 --> 00:00:46.576
[ Cheering ]
- [ Whistles Blowing ]...

9
00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:49.589
? [ Salsa ]

10
00:01:00.727 --> 00:01:03.841
You've made me
very happy. my dear.

11
00:01:03.945 --> 00:01:05.843
l am happy too.

12
00:01:05.947 --> 00:01:08.600
l wish only that your son
would have come to our wedding.

13
00:01:08.704 --> 00:01:11.765
My son has problems.
- How can he have problems...

14
00:01:11.869 --> 00:01:13.177
with a father like you?

15
00:01:13.282 --> 00:01:15.979
He has problems
because he has a father like me.

16
00:01:16.083 --> 00:01:18.984
[ Man Shouting In Portugese ]
- [ Camera Shutter Clicking ]...

17
00:01:19.088 --> 00:01:22.193
[ Man ] Dear Walter. wedding snap
of me and your new mom.

18
00:01:22.297 --> 00:01:25.414
We won't be coming to New York
for the 2.9 million reasons...

19
00:01:25.518 --> 00:01:26.983
you are aware of. Love. Dad.

20
00:01:27.087 --> 00:01:28.675
P.S. Give my best
to the Cheap Girls.

21
00:01:28.779 --> 00:01:29.746
They were my favourite.

22
00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:31.744
[ Woman ]
Very pretty. your new mom.

23
00:01:31.848 --> 00:01:34.162
We used to be a respectable
law firm. Now look at him.

24
00:01:34.266 --> 00:01:35.137
Looks happy to me.

25
00:01:35.241 --> 00:01:37.087
He steals the money. l get the bills.

26
00:01:37.191 --> 00:01:39.251
Dad. why did you do this to me?

27
00:01:39.356 --> 00:01:41.669
Well. l can see why.
- Good night. Walter.

28
00:01:41.774 --> 00:01:43.666
[ Lamp Switch Clicking Off ]...

29
00:01:43.770 --> 00:01:50.053
??

30
00:01:50.157 --> 00:01:52.056
? I feel your every breath...

31
00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:54.730
? I hear the words you say...

32
00:01:57.784 --> 00:01:59.356
? And I keep turning back...

33
00:01:59.460 --> 00:02:01.524
? To hear the music play...

34
00:02:01.628 --> 00:02:04.109
[ Echoing ]? Play...

35
00:02:04.213 --> 00:02:06.156
? I'll make no promises...

36
00:02:06.261 --> 00:02:10.379
? False promises can break you...

37
00:02:11.632 --> 00:02:13.913
? How can you call me home...

38
00:02:14.017 --> 00:02:17.093
? Wanting me like yesterday...

39
00:02:19.890 --> 00:02:21.461
? Where do we build a house...

40
00:02:21.566 --> 00:02:24.132
? How do the roses grow...

41
00:02:27.147 --> 00:02:28.801
? Are you and I in love...

42
00:02:28.905 --> 00:02:31.604
? How do we really know...

43
00:02:33.487 --> 00:02:35.601
? If love is on our side...

44
00:02:35.706 --> 00:02:39.398
? You'll know when I'm in trouble...

45
00:02:40.953 --> 00:02:42.901
? That's when my heart decides...

46
00:02:43.006 --> 00:02:46.163
? To go wherever you will go...

47
00:02:48.502 --> 00:02:51.909
? The heart is so willing...

48
00:02:52.014 --> 00:02:54.543
? To follow...

49
00:02:55.843 --> 00:02:57.913
? The heart shows the way...

50
00:02:58.018 --> 00:03:00.419
? Out of the night...

51
00:03:03.016 --> 00:03:04.920
? The heart roams...

52
00:03:05.025 --> 00:03:09.063
? In search of tomorrow...

53
00:03:10.357 --> 00:03:12.261
? When your love takes...

54
00:03:12.365 --> 00:03:15.185
? The hand that guides the light...

55
00:03:15.289 --> 00:03:17.852
[ Echoing ]? Light...

56
00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:24.044
[ Walter ] ''New mom.''
How old is that girl?

57
00:03:24.148 --> 00:03:25.727
[ Woman ] Good morning. Walter.

58
00:03:25.831 --> 00:03:28.739
Don't they have any laws in Brazil?
Don't they have any police?

59
00:03:28.843 --> 00:03:31.742
[ Woman ]
Don't be so conventional.

60
00:03:31.846 --> 00:03:35.495
[ Scoffs ]
I'm a conventional kind of guy.

61
00:03:35.599 --> 00:03:38.499
That's all l ever wanted to be.
just conventional.

62
00:03:38.603 --> 00:03:41.124
A little house in the suburbs.
a white picket fence...

63
00:03:41.229 --> 00:03:43.458
maybe a dog.
2.4 kids...

64
00:03:43.562 --> 00:03:46.338
and just to round it out-- a wife.

65
00:03:46.442 --> 00:03:48.641
Will you marry me?

66
00:03:50.272 --> 00:03:52.357
Walter...

67
00:03:52.447 --> 00:03:54.594
[ Sighs ] my darling...

68
00:03:54.698 --> 00:03:57.013
I love you very much.

69
00:03:57.117 --> 00:03:59.250
But why do we need
a piece of paper...

70
00:03:59.354 --> 00:04:00.853
from the state of New York?

71
00:04:00.958 --> 00:04:06.392
One bad experience. that's all.
You just had one bad experience.

72
00:04:06.497 --> 00:04:09.361
Just give me a little more time.

73
00:04:09.465 --> 00:04:12.127
[ Sighs ] Okay.

74
00:04:12.586 --> 00:04:15.911
But l can't live
this life of shame much longer.

75
00:04:16.015 --> 00:04:20.004
You're gonna have to make
an honest man of me.

76
00:04:20.677 --> 00:04:24.311
l like the kissing part.
- [ Giggling ]...

77
00:04:24.356 --> 00:04:27.212
[ Door Opening. Closing ]
- [ Men Chattering In Russian ]...

78
00:04:27.316 --> 00:04:29.712
Did you hear that?
- What?

79
00:04:29.817 --> 00:04:31.715
Somebody just came in
our front door.

80
00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:34.639
[ Chattering Continues ]...

81
00:04:34.744 --> 00:04:38.998
Be careful. Walter.
- [ Bedroom Door Opening ]...

82
00:04:39.822 --> 00:04:43.102
Oh. my God! You're still here?
- [ Laughing ]

83
00:04:43.206 --> 00:04:46.397
Boat has docked.
He's here. you're out.

84
00:04:46.501 --> 00:04:48.648
Who the hell are you?

85
00:04:48.752 --> 00:04:52.072
[ Speaking Russian ]
Maestro is back!

86
00:04:52.177 --> 00:04:55.242
l thought he wasn't coming back
until next week.

87
00:04:55.346 --> 00:04:58.163
[ Speaking Russian ]

88
00:04:58.267 --> 00:05:00.999
You know Maestro.
He surprise you.

89
00:05:01.103 --> 00:05:02.958
What are you talking about?
Who is this guy?

90
00:05:03.062 --> 00:05:04.465
l thought l had a year.

91
00:05:04.569 --> 00:05:06.794
You did. but year
has come and gone.

92
00:05:06.899 --> 00:05:10.420
[ Speaking Russian ] What you do?
You stayed in bed all the time?

93
00:05:10.524 --> 00:05:12.423
Didn't look for apartment?

94
00:05:12.527 --> 00:05:15.763
l... did.
There are no apartments.

95
00:05:15.867 --> 00:05:18.388
Yeah. right.

96
00:05:18.492 --> 00:05:21.599
Who are we talking about?
Who is this guy? Who are you?

97
00:05:21.703 --> 00:05:23.601
l'm talking to him.
he won't answer me.

98
00:05:23.705 --> 00:05:25.714
When is he coming here?
- [ Man ] Oh. maybe...

99
00:05:25.819 --> 00:05:26.931
a minute. maybe an hour.

100
00:05:27.035 --> 00:05:29.484
But he will come.

101
00:05:29.588 --> 00:05:32.943
lt's him you're talking about.
isn't it? The lunatic is back.

102
00:05:33.048 --> 00:05:35.361
Yes!

103
00:05:35.466 --> 00:05:37.575
l thought he was in Europe.

104
00:05:37.679 --> 00:05:42.022
[ Man ] He was.
and now he's back. and you're out!

105
00:05:42.217 --> 00:05:44.454
Oh. All right.
l'm sorry.

106
00:05:44.558 --> 00:05:47.795
Look. guys.
why don't l talk to him.

107
00:05:47.899 --> 00:05:50.338
Maybe we can
live here all together.

108
00:05:50.442 --> 00:05:52.569
[ Laughing. Chattering ]

109
00:05:53.854 --> 00:05:55.968
Wait. Wait.
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

110
00:05:56.073 --> 00:05:58.135
You're not lookin' at
a charity case here.

111
00:05:58.240 --> 00:06:01.724
lf this is his apartment.
we'll get out. lt's no problem.

112
00:06:01.829 --> 00:06:04.728
Could you just give us
a few minutes alone?

113
00:06:04.833 --> 00:06:07.935
Sure. l understand.
Have a nice day.

114
00:06:10.245 --> 00:06:12.482
What are we gonna do?

115
00:06:12.586 --> 00:06:14.410
This is New York City.
lt takes months...

116
00:06:14.514 --> 00:06:16.155
to find a place. even if you're rich.

117
00:06:16.260 --> 00:06:17.322
And we're broke!

118
00:06:17.426 --> 00:06:19.742
We're doomed.
homeless. penniless.

119
00:06:19.847 --> 00:06:22.664
Doomed.
- l'm sorry. Walter.

120
00:06:22.768 --> 00:06:24.914
No. no. no. lt's not your fault.

121
00:06:25.018 --> 00:06:27.164
We both knew he
was coming back.

122
00:06:27.269 --> 00:06:30.421
lt's just that we've
been so happy lately.

123
00:06:30.525 --> 00:06:32.836
Jack can help us.

124
00:06:32.940 --> 00:06:35.025
lsn't Jack in jail?

125
00:06:35.070 --> 00:06:37.133
No. No. he got off
with a small fine.

126
00:06:37.237 --> 00:06:40.225
Jack's a perfectly legitimate
real estate agent.

127
00:06:40.330 --> 00:06:40.838
[ Sighs ]

128
00:06:40.943 --> 00:06:43.430
Well. as long as we're together.

129
00:06:43.534 --> 00:06:47.602
Nothing bad can happen.
- Mmm.

130
00:06:47.707 --> 00:06:49.464
[ Woman ] Good morning.
Realty Office.

131
00:06:49.568 --> 00:06:50.896
Oh. here's a beautiful place.

132
00:06:51.001 --> 00:06:53.192
lt's only an eight-hour commute
to New York City.

133
00:06:53.297 --> 00:06:55.192
You don't get in more
than once a week. do you?

134
00:06:55.297 --> 00:06:56.756
[ Walter On Phone ]
I'll even go to SoHo.

135
00:06:56.861 --> 00:06:58.320
I looked at a loft
there a few years ago.

136
00:06:58.425 --> 00:07:01.699
It was $350 a month.
It's probably gone up. but--

137
00:07:01.803 --> 00:07:05.204
SoHo. 350 a month. Let's see.
Eisenhower was president. right?

138
00:07:05.309 --> 00:07:08.208
I'm worried. Jack. I'm very worried.
- [ Buzzing ]

139
00:07:08.313 --> 00:07:10.457
Listen. Walter.
l gotta take a call.

140
00:07:10.561 --> 00:07:12.460
Meet me at
the jogging track at 1:00.

141
00:07:12.564 --> 00:07:15.505
You won't recognize me.
l'm so thin!

142
00:07:15.610 --> 00:07:19.066
Where have you been?
You're almost late.

143
00:07:19.153 --> 00:07:20.109
Martha. in this country...

144
00:07:20.213 --> 00:07:21.634
we have an expression
for almost late.

145
00:07:21.739 --> 00:07:24.015
lt's called ''on time.''

146
00:07:24.119 --> 00:07:26.264
You don't seem nervous.
- l'm not.

147
00:07:26.368 --> 00:07:28.811
[ Chuckling ]
She's not nervous. l'm nervous.

148
00:07:28.916 --> 00:07:30.895
You're hysterical.

149
00:07:30.999 --> 00:07:32.897
How is Walter taking it?

150
00:07:33.001 --> 00:07:36.236
Taking what?
There's nothing to take.

151
00:07:36.341 --> 00:07:38.538
[ Gasps ] Here he comes!

152
00:07:49.845 --> 00:07:52.414
Thank you. thank you.
thank you. thank you. thank you.

153
00:07:52.518 --> 00:07:55.756
lt's a great pleasure
to be back with you again.

154
00:07:55.860 --> 00:07:57.922
l'm sure you feel the same.
- [ Sparse Laughter ]

155
00:07:58.026 --> 00:08:01.262
When l left. you were
the finest orchestra in the world.

156
00:08:01.366 --> 00:08:04.935
God knows what a season under
the heavy hand of my esteemed...

157
00:08:05.039 --> 00:08:06.299
colleague has wrought.

158
00:08:06.403 --> 00:08:09.267
Let us assess the damage...

159
00:08:09.372 --> 00:08:12.698
with the Haydn.
from the beginning.

160
00:08:15.078 --> 00:08:18.032
?? [ Begins ]...

161
00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:35.336
? Bring me higher and higher?

162
00:08:35.440 --> 00:08:37.381
? Give me lovin'?

163
00:08:37.485 --> 00:08:39.712
? P-Please me tonight...

164
00:08:39.817 --> 00:08:43.969
Jimmy!
- Watch it. Watch it.

165
00:08:44.073 --> 00:08:46.347
?? [ Continues ]
- Jimmy!

166
00:08:46.451 --> 00:08:48.974
Big guy! Big ''W.'' What's shakin'?

167
00:08:49.078 --> 00:08:51.685
l've got some papers.
The band has to sign these.

168
00:08:51.789 --> 00:08:53.914
What is it?
- Well. it's the Roy Rogers...

169
00:08:54.018 --> 00:08:55.682
restaurants we bought into...

170
00:08:55.786 --> 00:08:58.567
and l sold off the Tucson property.

171
00:08:58.671 --> 00:09:01.489
This is their share.
and this is mine.

172
00:09:01.594 --> 00:09:05.325
Now. l figure that cancels out
half my father's debt...

173
00:09:05.429 --> 00:09:08.079
but check your records.
make sure we agree.

174
00:09:08.184 --> 00:09:10.881
Walter. what are you
payin' them back for?

175
00:09:10.985 --> 00:09:11.280
Huh?

176
00:09:11.385 --> 00:09:13.621
They're used to people
stealin' from 'em.

177
00:09:13.726 --> 00:09:15.341
This is only gonna confuse 'em.

178
00:09:15.445 --> 00:09:17.545
They've got too much
money now as it is.

179
00:09:17.649 --> 00:09:20.549
You're their manager.
Why are you telling me this?

180
00:09:20.653 --> 00:09:23.175
Because l like you better
than l like them.

181
00:09:23.279 --> 00:09:26.972
But they're your sister
and your brothers.

182
00:09:30.612 --> 00:09:32.901
? [ Ends ]

183
00:09:44.459 --> 00:09:47.480
The union forces me to
allow you to go to...

184
00:09:47.584 --> 00:09:50.326
lunch in spite of the
way you've played.

185
00:09:50.430 --> 00:09:53.621
Those of you with consciences
will not be able to eat.

186
00:09:53.725 --> 00:09:55.308
And those of you
whose consciences...

187
00:09:55.412 --> 00:09:56.288
match your talents...

188
00:09:56.392 --> 00:09:58.292
go stuff yourselves.

189
00:09:58.396 --> 00:10:00.505
l hope you choke.

190
00:10:00.609 --> 00:10:02.549
Jog with me. Wally.

191
00:10:02.654 --> 00:10:04.676
l don't wanna break my rhythm.

192
00:10:04.780 --> 00:10:08.004
How long have you
been doing this. Jack?

193
00:10:08.108 --> 00:10:10.089
Oh. six months. lt's great.

194
00:10:10.194 --> 00:10:12.452
Next month l'm
gonna run in a 1 -K.

195
00:10:12.556 --> 00:10:13.890
Would you believe it?

196
00:10:13.994 --> 00:10:17.064
Before l started this.
l couldn't fit into these clothes.

197
00:10:17.168 --> 00:10:20.067
l feel better. l look better.
l sweat better.

198
00:10:20.171 --> 00:10:22.066
So you called my office.
- [ Beeping ]...

199
00:10:22.170 --> 00:10:24.168
Do you have some
good news for me?

200
00:10:24.272 --> 00:10:24.823
Good news?

201
00:10:24.927 --> 00:10:26.407
When you hear what l got for you.

202
00:10:26.511 --> 00:10:28.408
just remember this is
a conservative club.

203
00:10:28.512 --> 00:10:30.574
Don't rip off my shoes
and kiss my feet.

204
00:10:30.679 --> 00:10:33.076
You don't have to worry about that.
- [ Grunts ]

205
00:10:33.180 --> 00:10:37.120
You asked for an apartment?
Something nice. yet affordable?

206
00:10:37.225 --> 00:10:39.585
Uh. Jack. could you sweat
the other way. please?

207
00:10:39.690 --> 00:10:44.088
Wally. will you listen to me?
- Not if you keep calling me Wally.

208
00:10:44.192 --> 00:10:45.389
[ Beeping Resumes ]
- Oh.

209
00:10:45.493 --> 00:10:46.084
What is that?

210
00:10:46.188 --> 00:10:48.757
Oh. it's nothing.
lt's a pulse alarm.

211
00:10:48.861 --> 00:10:50.828
Well. maybe we should stop.
- No. no. no.

212
00:10:50.932 --> 00:10:52.256
These things are unreliable.

213
00:10:52.361 --> 00:10:54.463
Walter. can you get your hands on...

214
00:10:54.567 --> 00:10:56.729
$200.000 by close
of business Friday?

215
00:10:56.833 --> 00:10:58.728
[ Beeping Accelerating ]
- Well. let me see.

216
00:10:58.832 --> 00:11:02.650
lf l sell everything l own.
maybe l can buy you lunch.

217
00:11:02.754 --> 00:11:04.650
[ Gasping ]
- Jack?

218
00:11:04.754 --> 00:11:07.862
[ Gasping Continues ]
- Jack? Jack. are you all right?

219
00:11:07.966 --> 00:11:11.701
[ Siren Wailing ]...

220
00:11:11.805 --> 00:11:15.122
l'm fine. really.
- Take it easy. Mr Schnittman.

221
00:11:15.226 --> 00:11:17.665
Has this ever happened before?
- Yeah.

222
00:11:17.769 --> 00:11:20.165
Seven times
in the past five months.

223
00:11:20.269 --> 00:11:22.992
l thought jogging was getting you
in better shape.

224
00:11:23.097 --> 00:11:23.287
lt is.

225
00:11:23.392 --> 00:11:25.052
Yeah. Thanks to the jogging.

226
00:11:25.156 --> 00:11:27.427
now l can lift him
into the ambulance.

227
00:11:27.531 --> 00:11:30.679
Walter. this is
a million-dollar house. literally.

228
00:11:30.784 --> 00:11:32.576
l just want an apartment.
My girlfriend's...

229
00:11:32.680 --> 00:11:34.220
ex-husband returned
from Europe today.

230
00:11:34.325 --> 00:11:36.223
That's nice.

231
00:11:36.328 --> 00:11:38.560
No. we have to get
out of his place now.

232
00:11:38.664 --> 00:11:40.440
It's an uncomfortable situation.

233
00:11:40.544 --> 00:11:44.608
Why would somebody sell
a million-dollar house for 200.000?

234
00:11:44.712 --> 00:11:48.568
Who knows?
A divorce. loan sharks...

235
00:11:48.672 --> 00:11:50.571
drugs. sudden death.

236
00:11:50.675 --> 00:11:52.895
The point is: You get to capitalize...

237
00:11:52.999 --> 00:11:55.159
on a fellow human
being's misfortune.

238
00:11:55.263 --> 00:11:59.331
That's the basis of real estate.
Have we got a deal?

239
00:11:59.435 --> 00:12:01.358
? [ Classical ]
- [ Maestro ] You are...

240
00:12:01.462 --> 00:12:02.869
more beautiful than ever.

241
00:12:02.973 --> 00:12:04.877
Thank you. So are you.
- [ Chattering ]

242
00:12:04.981 --> 00:12:07.006
Why did we ever get divorced?

243
00:12:07.110 --> 00:12:10.567
So we could look better.
for one reason.

244
00:12:10.649 --> 00:12:12.735
Hmm.

245
00:12:12.816 --> 00:12:16.013
Can l speak frankly?
- Anything's possible.

246
00:12:16.117 --> 00:12:17.047
Anna. l have learned...

247
00:12:17.152 --> 00:12:18.809
that my life is
meaningless without you.

248
00:12:18.913 --> 00:12:21.020
l know we made
a mess of things before...

249
00:12:21.124 --> 00:12:24.524
but l wanna put the past behind us
and begin again fresh...

250
00:12:24.628 --> 00:12:27.445
and at the same time
older and wiser.

251
00:12:27.550 --> 00:12:29.443
Can we do that?
- No.

252
00:12:29.547 --> 00:12:32.533
What do you mean ''no''? Why not?
- l love Walter.

253
00:12:32.637 --> 00:12:34.029
''Walter''? What Walter?

254
00:12:34.133 --> 00:12:36.369
Oh. Max. you know
exactly what Walter.

255
00:12:36.473 --> 00:12:39.226
Don't be ridiculous.
He's not even a musician.

256
00:12:39.330 --> 00:12:40.490
Many people aren't.

257
00:12:40.594 --> 00:12:42.709
Anna. please.
l have finally discovered...

258
00:12:42.813 --> 00:12:45.713
there is only one person
in the world who matters to me.

259
00:12:45.817 --> 00:12:48.377
And that's you.
l've known that for a long time.

260
00:12:48.481 --> 00:12:51.007
No. You love me.
and l love you.

261
00:12:51.112 --> 00:12:53.847
You love you.
I love Walter.

262
00:12:53.951 --> 00:12:59.352
Will you stop saying that?
- Max. it's over for us. Over.

263
00:12:59.457 --> 00:13:02.825
All right.
Then just go to bed with me.

264
00:13:02.831 --> 00:13:04.773
[ Ping-Pong Ball Bouncing ]

265
00:13:04.878 --> 00:13:06.325
A few of the Maestro's things.

266
00:13:06.429 --> 00:13:08.027
He moves back in
today. you know.

267
00:13:08.131 --> 00:13:10.396
Yeah. l know. Party's
over for you guys.

268
00:13:10.500 --> 00:13:11.779
You'll have to go home.

269
00:13:11.884 --> 00:13:14.157
Some girl called.
Said she'd taken a lot of pills...

270
00:13:14.261 --> 00:13:16.451
and was gonna kill herself
if you didn't call her.

271
00:13:16.555 --> 00:13:18.700
[ Walter ] No. no. I get those calls
two or three times a week.

272
00:13:18.804 --> 00:13:20.703
She really sounds bad.
- [ Doorbell Buzzing ]...

273
00:13:20.807 --> 00:13:22.971
l think she sounds awful.

274
00:13:23.075 --> 00:13:26.886
but she sold six million
records last year.

275
00:13:27.182 --> 00:13:29.398
Walter!
- Hey. how are ya?

276
00:13:29.485 --> 00:13:32.394
l gotta get some food right now!

277
00:13:36.233 --> 00:13:38.267
Okay. we promised never
to come to your...

278
00:13:38.372 --> 00:13:40.307
place again. but this
is a major crisis.

279
00:13:40.411 --> 00:13:42.308
lt's not my place any more.

280
00:13:42.412 --> 00:13:44.459
When your father
took all our money.

281
00:13:44.563 --> 00:13:45.852
you were so nice to us.

282
00:13:45.956 --> 00:13:48.036
You washed my hair.
l didn't forget that.

283
00:13:48.141 --> 00:13:48.641
? [ Piano ]

284
00:13:48.745 --> 00:13:51.027
We trust you.
We need your advice.

285
00:13:51.131 --> 00:13:53.610
l am sure l did not wash your hair.

286
00:13:53.714 --> 00:13:56.112
Look. l gotta get up early
tomorrow and go see Benny.

287
00:13:56.216 --> 00:13:58.115
You see Benny?
- [ Man ] He sees Benny?

288
00:13:58.220 --> 00:13:59.124
What's your problem?

289
00:13:59.228 --> 00:14:01.039
We want to change
the name of the band.

290
00:14:01.143 --> 00:14:03.620
You can't do that!
You've spent years and a fortune...

291
00:14:03.724 --> 00:14:05.623
to make your name
a household word.

292
00:14:05.727 --> 00:14:08.463
Your name is perfect.
''Cheap Girls.'' l love it.

293
00:14:08.567 --> 00:14:11.250
l'm not sure it's us.
- [ Burps ]...

294
00:14:11.355 --> 00:14:11.706
lt is.

295
00:14:11.810 --> 00:14:13.693
We wanna call ourselves
''Meryl Streep.''...

296
00:14:13.798 --> 00:14:14.840
[ Man Shouting ]

297
00:14:14.945 --> 00:14:18.596
No. no. You cannot call yourselves
''Meryl Streep.''

298
00:14:18.700 --> 00:14:21.556
Maybe she'll be flattered.
- No. in fact. considering your act...

299
00:14:21.661 --> 00:14:23.641
l think l can guarantee
a giant lawsuit.

300
00:14:23.745 --> 00:14:26.020
? [ Piano Continues ]
- [ Clattering ]

301
00:14:26.124 --> 00:14:28.020
Don't take off your coat.
Forget it.

302
00:14:28.124 --> 00:14:30.316
You are not calling yourselves
''Meryl Streep.''

303
00:14:30.420 --> 00:14:32.340
Come on. we're gonna
go see a house.

304
00:14:32.444 --> 00:14:33.487
A house? Where?

305
00:14:33.591 --> 00:14:35.697
An hour away from everyone.

306
00:14:35.801 --> 00:14:39.080
[ Man ]
How about ''Debbie Reynolds''?

307
00:14:43.050 --> 00:14:45.975
Thanks very much.
Keep the change.

308
00:14:48.430 --> 00:14:51.621
This can't be it.
- lt's the address.

309
00:14:53.268 --> 00:14:55.799
[ Anna ] It's beautiful.

310
00:14:55.903 --> 00:14:58.510
l know.
Somethin' must be wrong.

311
00:14:58.614 --> 00:15:01.727
Well. let's go see.

312
00:15:03.779 --> 00:15:07.021
Hi! Come on in.
- [ Anna ] Thank you.

313
00:15:07.125 --> 00:15:09.602
? [ Classical ]...

314
00:15:09.707 --> 00:15:12.860
[ Door Closes ]

315
00:15:12.964 --> 00:15:15.049
Mmm.

316
00:15:16.124 --> 00:15:19.072
Excuse the way the place looks.

317
00:15:19.176 --> 00:15:22.077
l really let it go to hell
since Carlos left.

318
00:15:22.182 --> 00:15:25.497
But the house is beautiful.

319
00:15:25.602 --> 00:15:28.834
Carlos and l were very happy here.

320
00:15:28.938 --> 00:15:31.793
lt's all over now.
The living room's in here.

321
00:15:31.898 --> 00:15:35.004
This is great.
- Fabulous.

322
00:15:35.108 --> 00:15:38.843
Listen. if you want
any of the furniture. it's all for sale.

323
00:15:38.947 --> 00:15:42.469
Well. l think that we'd like
to decorate it ourselves.

324
00:15:42.573 --> 00:15:46.513
l'd sell it cheap.
l need all the money l can get.

325
00:15:46.617 --> 00:15:49.977
Goddam bloodsucking lawyers
are bleeding me dry.

326
00:15:50.081 --> 00:15:52.440
[ Chuckling ]

327
00:15:52.544 --> 00:15:57.773
The floor just needs a little polish.
The bedroom's up here.

328
00:15:58.458 --> 00:16:00.913
l'm trying to save a
few bucks on the...

329
00:16:01.017 --> 00:16:03.409
lights... for the
bloodsucking lawyers.

330
00:16:03.514 --> 00:16:06.619
I think it's lovely.
- [ Stairs Creaking ]

331
00:16:06.723 --> 00:16:10.889
There's a tricky step.
l keep meaning to fix it.

332
00:16:12.306 --> 00:16:15.131
What a beautiful bed.

333
00:16:15.236 --> 00:16:16.534
Could l use your bathroom?

334
00:16:16.638 --> 00:16:18.300
Would you use the
one downstairs?

335
00:16:18.404 --> 00:16:21.176
All my personal things
are still in this one.

336
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:23.366
Oh. Sure.

337
00:16:25.402 --> 00:16:29.227
Happiest moments of my life
since we left Paraguay...

338
00:16:29.331 --> 00:16:32.020
have been spent
right here in this room.

339
00:16:32.124 --> 00:16:34.021
You lived in Paraguay?

340
00:16:34.125 --> 00:16:36.606
Ten wonderful years.

341
00:16:36.710 --> 00:16:39.540
Carlos is from Asuncion.

342
00:16:40.709 --> 00:16:43.959
Or at least he-- [ Weeping ]...

343
00:16:51.261 --> 00:16:53.626
l'm awfully sorry.

344
00:16:53.730 --> 00:16:55.816
About what?

345
00:16:57.184 --> 00:16:59.088
l don't know actually.

346
00:16:59.192 --> 00:17:01.634
Do you wanna buy the bed?

347
00:17:01.738 --> 00:17:04.472
l-l think so.

348
00:17:04.577 --> 00:17:09.766
You know. you think
you know somebody...

349
00:17:09.871 --> 00:17:12.061
after 25 years...

350
00:17:12.166 --> 00:17:14.394
and then one day...

351
00:17:14.498 --> 00:17:17.523
lsraeli lntelligence
comes to the door.

352
00:17:17.627 --> 00:17:19.525
lsraeli lntelligence?

353
00:17:19.629 --> 00:17:20.863
Last Tuesday.

354
00:17:20.967 --> 00:17:24.574
That's why l've
gotta sell the house.

355
00:17:24.678 --> 00:17:28.881
lt turns out.
Carlos was Hitler's pool man.

356
00:17:30.634 --> 00:17:33.635
[ Toilet Flushing ]
- Mm-hmm.

357
00:17:37.307 --> 00:17:39.393
Ouch!

358
00:17:43.438 --> 00:17:46.929
There's a lot of grounds.
but the maintenance isn't too bad.

359
00:17:47.034 --> 00:17:49.869
l've always done it myself.
but you could hire a gardener.

360
00:17:49.973 --> 00:17:51.050
''A gardener''? No. no.

361
00:17:51.155 --> 00:17:54.846
l could handle this.
This'd be a piece of cake.

362
00:17:54.950 --> 00:17:57.035
[ Anna ] Really?

363
00:17:57.085 --> 00:18:00.191
[ Car Horn Honking ]...

364
00:18:00.295 --> 00:18:02.109
[ Brakes Screeching ]
- [ Anna ] Fabulous car!

365
00:18:02.213 --> 00:18:04.111
What's it called again?
- lt's a Lincoln.

366
00:18:04.215 --> 00:18:05.715
They don't make 'em
like this any more.

367
00:18:05.819 --> 00:18:06.324
lt's a beauty.

368
00:18:06.428 --> 00:18:09.201
Do you like it? l'll throw it in
if you buy the house.

369
00:18:09.305 --> 00:18:11.390
That's very generous.

370
00:18:11.473 --> 00:18:14.125
l'm desperate.
Can we close?

371
00:18:14.230 --> 00:18:16.456
Well. we need a little time to--

372
00:18:16.560 --> 00:18:19.042
There isn't any time.
Extradition is Friday.

373
00:18:19.146 --> 00:18:22.338
Extradition?
- l'll tell you later.

374
00:18:22.442 --> 00:18:24.620
l need an answer
by close of business tomorrow.

375
00:18:24.725 --> 00:18:25.918
[ Walter ] Oh. you'll have it.

376
00:18:26.023 --> 00:18:28.305
By the way. you have the most...

377
00:18:28.409 --> 00:18:31.057
beautifully kept
pool l've ever seen.

378
00:18:31.161 --> 00:18:34.560
Oh. God. Oh. God.
[ Weeping ]...

379
00:18:34.665 --> 00:18:37.226
[ Walter ] What did l say?

380
00:18:37.330 --> 00:18:39.415
What did l say?

381
00:18:40.954 --> 00:18:44.280
Jack was right.
We can't lose.

382
00:18:44.384 --> 00:18:45.937
Nothing can be this easy.

383
00:18:46.042 --> 00:18:48.238
Sure it can. You know what this is?

384
00:18:48.342 --> 00:18:52.259
This is the short line
in Motor Vehicles.

385
00:18:52.364 --> 00:18:52.955
What?

386
00:18:53.059 --> 00:18:55.081
You go to Motor Vehicles
to get your licence renewed...

387
00:18:55.185 --> 00:18:57.625
and you get on this line
that reaches to Spain.

388
00:18:57.729 --> 00:19:00.713
And right next to it is this little
short line with only two guys on it.

389
00:19:00.817 --> 00:19:02.408
But you don't get on
that line. 'cause you...

390
00:19:02.512 --> 00:19:03.921
think something must
be wrong with it...

391
00:19:04.025 --> 00:19:07.299
otherwise everybody else would be
on it. so you waste three hours.

392
00:19:07.404 --> 00:19:11.343
l got on the short line once.
lt was for farm vehicles.

393
00:19:11.447 --> 00:19:14.469
l want this house.
l need this house.

394
00:19:14.573 --> 00:19:16.100
We need this house.

395
00:19:16.204 --> 00:19:19.781
Could be great.
- Say ''yes''!

396
00:19:23.080 --> 00:19:25.400
lf we do this.
we do it together.

397
00:19:25.504 --> 00:19:28.612
l'm putting in half the money.
or l'm not going in.

398
00:19:28.717 --> 00:19:29.759
Great!

399
00:19:29.864 --> 00:19:32.701
l thought you'd give
me an argument.

400
00:19:32.805 --> 00:19:34.853
lf l had any money. l would.

401
00:19:34.957 --> 00:19:37.455
Where are you gonna
get your half?

402
00:19:37.559 --> 00:19:39.644
Max.

403
00:19:39.644 --> 00:19:43.334
I'll sell him everything I got in
the divorce. What about your half?

404
00:19:43.439 --> 00:19:46.841
l'm goin' straight to the top on this
one-- Billboard's Artist of the Year.

405
00:19:46.945 --> 00:19:50.351
He. who last year alone
sold 22 million records.

406
00:19:50.455 --> 00:19:50.962
Benny?

407
00:19:51.066 --> 00:19:53.680
Yeah.
- Benny himself?

408
00:19:53.784 --> 00:19:58.100
[ Train Horn Blaring ]
- Did you hear that?

409
00:19:58.204 --> 00:20:01.689
The train is coming. right when
we decided to buy the house!

410
00:20:01.793 --> 00:20:04.272
[ Train Horn Blaring Continues ]
- This has got to be an omen.

411
00:20:04.376 --> 00:20:09.251
l can feel it! This is it!
Everything's breaking for us!

412
00:20:19.470 --> 00:20:22.305
? [ TVCartoon ]

413
00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:25.544
You say you have an appointment?

414
00:20:25.649 --> 00:20:26.614
l don't say l have...

415
00:20:26.718 --> 00:20:28.507
an appointment. l
have an appointment!

416
00:20:28.611 --> 00:20:30.508
Hi. Mr Fielding.
- Hello.

417
00:20:30.612 --> 00:20:32.322
[ Boy ] What the
hell does he want?

418
00:20:32.426 --> 00:20:33.431
[ Man ] I don't know.

419
00:20:33.536 --> 00:20:34.933
[ Boy ] Didn't you ask him? What's...

420
00:20:35.037 --> 00:20:36.433
the matter. I gotta
pay you to think?

421
00:20:36.538 --> 00:20:39.436
[ Man ] Hejust told me he wants
to see you. Sorry. Benny.

422
00:20:39.541 --> 00:20:42.945
Oh. well. that makes
everything better.

423
00:20:43.049 --> 00:20:45.016
Walter. how are ya?

424
00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:48.900
Okay. you've seen me. ls that it.
or do you wanna talk too?

425
00:20:49.004 --> 00:20:50.903
l wanna talk.

426
00:20:51.007 --> 00:20:53.238
Figures.

427
00:20:53.342 --> 00:20:56.495
[ TV] Now I'll show you how easy
I can catch a woodpecker.

428
00:20:56.599 --> 00:20:59.787
All right.
You've got five minutes.

429
00:20:59.891 --> 00:21:02.000
Are you gonna let her do that?

430
00:21:02.104 --> 00:21:06.092
Are you gonna let my mother
clean that carpet?

431
00:21:06.183 --> 00:21:09.108
Thanks. Benny.
- Don't mention it.

432
00:21:09.151 --> 00:21:11.631
I made a nice pot roast.
- Don't mention that either.

433
00:21:11.735 --> 00:21:13.883
[ Chuckling ] He never eats.

434
00:21:13.988 --> 00:21:17.928
Look. Mom. we're real busy here.
Why don't you go watch TV?

435
00:21:18.032 --> 00:21:21.641
Hey. keep it brief.
l got a chick waiting in the Jacuzzi.

436
00:21:21.745 --> 00:21:25.323
l wish l had
a hundred more like him.

437
00:21:27.746 --> 00:21:30.738
There is a house l want to buy.

438
00:21:30.842 --> 00:21:34.446
Let's just cut to the chase. okay?
What do you want?

439
00:21:34.550 --> 00:21:38.996
l want you to loan me
$200.000 in cash.

440
00:21:39.100 --> 00:21:41.186
No.

441
00:21:41.885 --> 00:21:43.706
Benny!
- [ Weapon Clicks ]...

442
00:21:43.810 --> 00:21:46.252
You shout at me?
- I shout at you!

443
00:21:46.356 --> 00:21:48.335
l need that money.
and you're gonna loan it to me!

444
00:21:48.440 --> 00:21:51.508
l will not! No! No! No!
- Yes. you will.

445
00:21:51.613 --> 00:21:55.428
Yes. you will! l saved you
ten times that in taxes last year!

446
00:21:55.532 --> 00:21:57.838
So what?
- Benny. if you don't...

447
00:21:57.942 --> 00:21:59.882
loan me that money. l'll--...

448
00:21:59.987 --> 00:22:04.727
You'll what. huh? You'll what?
- l'll not like you any more!

449
00:22:04.831 --> 00:22:07.530
[ TVContinues ]...

450
00:22:12.124 --> 00:22:14.959
All right.
- Thanks.

451
00:22:16.795 --> 00:22:18.699
[ Telephone Ringing ]
- [ Jack ] Great!

452
00:22:18.803 --> 00:22:20.912
Great!
- [ Telephone Hangs Up ]...

453
00:22:21.016 --> 00:22:23.373
They bought it! All right. gang!
- [ Cheering. Applauding ]

454
00:22:23.477 --> 00:22:25.372
Way to go!
[ Coughing ]...

455
00:22:25.477 --> 00:22:28.306
[ Beeping ]
- Not again.

456
00:22:28.974 --> 00:22:31.382
? [ Pop ]...

457
00:22:35.147 --> 00:22:37.806
? Anyplace you would be...

458
00:22:37.910 --> 00:22:41.230
? Is certainly so perfectly
good for me...

459
00:22:41.334 --> 00:22:42.342
[ Clattering ]...

460
00:22:42.446 --> 00:22:45.975
? That any old hammer and nail
I find...

461
00:22:46.080 --> 00:22:49.649
? Just makes me high on sunshine
- [ Loud Clattering ]...

462
00:22:49.753 --> 00:22:52.359
? Settling in our duds...

463
00:22:52.463 --> 00:22:55.902
? Discovering the wonderful
highs of love...

464
00:22:56.006 --> 00:22:58.896
[ Coughing ]
- ? A little brush and polish...

465
00:22:59.000 --> 00:23:00.943
and you'll see what I mean...

466
00:23:01.048 --> 00:23:03.529
? We're sittin'on a dream...

467
00:23:04.343 --> 00:23:06.791
? Step through that door...

468
00:23:06.895 --> 00:23:10.505
? You'll see a grand room
with a view...

469
00:23:11.683 --> 00:23:16.144
? And a new moon for two
out there...

470
00:23:17.773 --> 00:23:23.101
? And just like real water
from those summer rains...

471
00:23:23.205 --> 00:23:26.186
? Don't you know...

472
00:23:26.291 --> 00:23:28.653
? Champagne will flow...

473
00:23:30.118 --> 00:23:33.149
? Gold dazzle ring
upon my finger...

474
00:23:33.253 --> 00:23:35.317
? Any stair we could climb...

475
00:23:35.422 --> 00:23:38.781
? Has got to be to heaven
and so divine...

476
00:23:38.886 --> 00:23:40.191
[ No Ringing ]...

477
00:23:40.295 --> 00:23:43.199
? That all we'll ever
have to do is lie around...

478
00:23:43.304 --> 00:23:43.820
[ Yelps ]...

479
00:23:43.924 --> 00:23:47.537
? And watch the stars above us
fall down...

480
00:23:47.641 --> 00:23:49.667
? We're callin'this mess our own...

481
00:23:49.771 --> 00:23:52.783
? And tellin'all the others
it's home. sweet home...

482
00:23:52.887 --> 00:23:54.122
[ Banging On Door ]...

483
00:23:54.226 --> 00:23:58.510
? If we were really closing in
on yesterday's mess...

484
00:23:58.615 --> 00:24:01.809
? We're both sittin' on a dream...

485
00:24:08.699 --> 00:24:11.653
[ Hammering Continues ]

486
00:24:21.628 --> 00:24:23.532
How's it going?

487
00:24:23.637 --> 00:24:27.410
Fine. What's that on your face?

488
00:24:27.514 --> 00:24:29.996
The ceiling.

489
00:24:30.100 --> 00:24:32.210
Seems to be coming down
in the bedroom.

490
00:24:32.314 --> 00:24:35.253
Oh. Well. l'll get to that later.
l only got two hands.

491
00:24:35.358 --> 00:24:37.676
Okay. [ Chuckling ]
- Okay.

492
00:24:40.272 --> 00:24:43.189
[ Groaning ]...

493
00:25:03.754 --> 00:25:07.328
[ Squeaking. Clanging ]...

494
00:25:07.432 --> 00:25:09.547
[ Clanging Continues ]

495
00:25:22.314 --> 00:25:24.679
What the hell was that?

496
00:25:24.783 --> 00:25:27.056
All l did was turn on the water.

497
00:25:27.161 --> 00:25:30.893
That's all?
- [ Squeaking. Banging ]

498
00:25:30.998 --> 00:25:32.893
That doesn't sound good.

499
00:25:32.998 --> 00:25:36.317
No.
You should see the--...

500
00:25:36.421 --> 00:25:38.776
l guess it's the water.

501
00:25:38.881 --> 00:25:41.025
l don't know. lt's revolting.
- Okay.

502
00:25:41.130 --> 00:25:43.822
So the plumbing's not perfect.

503
00:25:43.926 --> 00:25:46.406
We'll get it fixed.
lt's not the end of the world.

504
00:25:46.510 --> 00:25:49.580
You didn't see that water!
- Look. this is an old house.

505
00:25:49.684 --> 00:25:52.244
lt's gonna need some work.
You've gotta expect that.

506
00:25:52.348 --> 00:25:55.805
l didn't expect
that water. lt had legs.

507
00:25:55.894 --> 00:25:57.838
A little work.
a little care...

508
00:25:57.942 --> 00:26:00.502
a little imagination.
and it's gonna be great!

509
00:26:00.606 --> 00:26:03.089
lt's gonna be fun
fixing it up. You'll see.

510
00:26:03.193 --> 00:26:05.847
l don't know. l've never been
any good at that kind of thing.

511
00:26:05.951 --> 00:26:07.845
What kind of thing?
- Work.

512
00:26:07.949 --> 00:26:10.124
You can't go into it
with that kind of...

513
00:26:10.229 --> 00:26:12.349
attitude. You've gotta
be more positive.

514
00:26:12.454 --> 00:26:14.570
l'll try.
- Oh.

515
00:26:15.701 --> 00:26:18.814
A little care.
a little imagination...

516
00:26:18.919 --> 00:26:21.046
and a positive attitude.

517
00:26:23.542 --> 00:26:26.329
What was that?

518
00:26:27.588 --> 00:26:29.673
Nothing. dear.

519
00:27:00.662 --> 00:27:02.748
Son of a bitch.

520
00:27:05.751 --> 00:27:07.655
[ Squeals ]
- [ Yells ]...

521
00:27:07.759 --> 00:27:09.995
[ Screaming ]...

522
00:27:17.596 --> 00:27:20.083
[ Anna Shouting ]...

523
00:27:20.187 --> 00:27:22.491
[ Screaming Continues ]...

524
00:27:41.119 --> 00:27:43.956
Oh. Walter!
- The stairs are out!

525
00:27:44.790 --> 00:27:47.277
[ Yells ]

526
00:27:47.381 --> 00:27:49.863
Honey.
you're on my fingers.

527
00:27:49.967 --> 00:27:51.866
Oh-- [ Screaming ]...

528
00:27:51.970 --> 00:27:54.055
[ Crash ]

529
00:27:56.760 --> 00:27:58.846
Sorry.

530
00:28:00.222 --> 00:28:02.420
[ Kiss ]...

531
00:28:02.524 --> 00:28:05.268
[ Thunderclap ]...

532
00:28:06.812 --> 00:28:09.281
l'd help you with
that. but somebody...

533
00:28:09.385 --> 00:28:11.014
stepped on all my fingers.

534
00:28:11.118 --> 00:28:14.682
l said l was sorry.
- [ Thunder Continues ]...

535
00:28:14.786 --> 00:28:17.309
l didn't expect your fingers
to be on the floor.

536
00:28:17.413 --> 00:28:19.310
l know.
l'm just cranky.

537
00:28:19.414 --> 00:28:22.650
l guess it's having just thrown
$200.000 into the toilet.

538
00:28:22.754 --> 00:28:25.148
Either that or the intense pain.

539
00:28:25.252 --> 00:28:26.718
lt's only the first day.

540
00:28:26.822 --> 00:28:29.237
You're not gonna give
up on it already.

541
00:28:29.342 --> 00:28:32.199
Oh. yes. Yes. l am.
- Oh. no.

542
00:28:32.303 --> 00:28:34.661
No. you're not.
l'm not gonna let you.

543
00:28:34.765 --> 00:28:36.690
There's a chance we
could fob it off...

544
00:28:36.794 --> 00:28:37.704
on the Cheap Girls.

545
00:28:37.808 --> 00:28:39.954
We're not going to sell it.

546
00:28:40.059 --> 00:28:41.957
The land. at least.
has got to be worth something.

547
00:28:42.062 --> 00:28:45.169
The house is going to be great!

548
00:28:45.273 --> 00:28:47.926
Yeah. if we can peel the rind off it.

549
00:28:48.030 --> 00:28:52.510
What?
- lt's a lemon. honey. let's face it.

550
00:28:52.614 --> 00:28:54.556
You can't just quit.

551
00:28:54.661 --> 00:28:57.893
l'm a quitter.
and l'm not ready to quit yet.

552
00:28:57.997 --> 00:28:59.892
[ Walter ] Why not?

553
00:28:59.996 --> 00:29:03.020
[ Anna ] Commitment.
- [ Thunderclap ]...

554
00:29:03.124 --> 00:29:06.443
[ Walter ] Oh. That.

555
00:29:06.548 --> 00:29:09.025
You're right.
The house is gonna be great.

556
00:29:09.129 --> 00:29:11.698
I promise.
- [ Kiss ]...

557
00:29:13.003 --> 00:29:15.490
[ Thunder Continues ]...

558
00:29:15.594 --> 00:29:18.506
[ Water Pouring ]...

559
00:29:28.769 --> 00:29:30.551
[ Both Grunting ]
- Lady. this is impossible.

560
00:29:30.655 --> 00:29:32.662
[ Anna ] Oh. nonsense.
You're doing fine.

561
00:29:32.767 --> 00:29:33.920
l feel like l'm gonna die.

562
00:29:34.024 --> 00:29:36.972
You're not going to die.
l'm holding the ladder.

563
00:29:37.076 --> 00:29:40.598
lf you fall.
land on the mattress.

564
00:29:40.703 --> 00:29:42.301
Hello. Yes. Yes.
We're having some...

565
00:29:42.405 --> 00:29:44.227
problems with our
plumbing. and l was--...

566
00:29:44.331 --> 00:29:46.607
[ Man ] I can't move.
- Fielding. Walter Fielding.

567
00:29:46.712 --> 00:29:48.092
[ Men Grunting ]
- [ Anna ] Stop being a baby.

568
00:29:48.197 --> 00:29:48.768
You're nearly there.

569
00:29:48.872 --> 00:29:51.109
There's no reason why
you should've heard of me.

570
00:29:51.213 --> 00:29:53.157
I don't have any
references. I just--...

571
00:29:53.261 --> 00:29:56.993
Somebody here call a carpenter?
- Oh. yes. We did.

572
00:29:57.097 --> 00:29:59.619
[ Walter ] Yale. Yeah.

573
00:29:59.724 --> 00:30:02.165
Don't let go of the ladder!
- l wasn't really holding it. anyway.

574
00:30:02.269 --> 00:30:04.709
How much do l make a year?

575
00:30:04.813 --> 00:30:08.130
Uh. how much
do you make a year?

576
00:30:08.234 --> 00:30:10.129
Really?

577
00:30:10.233 --> 00:30:13.053
No. No. that's not a Jewish name.
- You're kidding. right?

578
00:30:13.157 --> 00:30:15.050
Get out of my life.
would you?

579
00:30:15.155 --> 00:30:17.489
[ Anna ] Don't touch me. pig!
- [ Man ] Oh. you're cute...

580
00:30:17.594 --> 00:30:18.339
when you're mad.

581
00:30:18.443 --> 00:30:20.347
I'm serious. Get away from me.
- Hey!

582
00:30:20.452 --> 00:30:23.393
Stop it!
- Hey. let go of her! That's my wife!

583
00:30:23.497 --> 00:30:25.394
Oh. yeah?
Well. l'm sorry.

584
00:30:25.498 --> 00:30:27.441
She didn't say nothin'
about being married.

585
00:30:27.545 --> 00:30:30.150
l just thought she was
good-lookin' wool.

586
00:30:30.254 --> 00:30:31.671
This animal attacked me!

587
00:30:31.776 --> 00:30:33.988
I didn't say anything
about anything.

588
00:30:34.092 --> 00:30:35.988
Look. l don't wanna cause trouble.

589
00:30:36.092 --> 00:30:38.950
lf l came on a little strong.
l'm sorry. okay?

590
00:30:39.055 --> 00:30:41.578
No. it's not okay.
- Just get out of here.

591
00:30:41.682 --> 00:30:45.166
Well. okay.
lf that's what you want.

592
00:30:45.270 --> 00:30:47.166
l think we should call the police.

593
00:30:47.270 --> 00:30:49.629
Hey. let's not get nuts here.

594
00:30:49.733 --> 00:30:51.674
[ Sighing ]
- Who are you anyway?

595
00:30:51.778 --> 00:30:56.469
Art Shirk. l'm the carpenter.
l think we spoke on the phone.

596
00:30:56.573 --> 00:30:59.845
You're the carpenter?
- Yeah. Well. l guess l'll be going.

597
00:30:59.950 --> 00:31:01.886
Oh. wait a minute!
Just wait a minute.

598
00:31:01.990 --> 00:31:03.351
Maybe we can clear this up.

599
00:31:03.455 --> 00:31:06.605
Clear this up?
What are you doing? He tried--...

600
00:31:06.709 --> 00:31:09.526
l know. but he's supposed to be
a really good carpenter.

601
00:31:09.630 --> 00:31:11.458
He tried to attack me.
- He just thought you were...

602
00:31:11.562 --> 00:31:12.268
good-lookin' wool--...

603
00:31:12.372 --> 00:31:14.276
an attractive woman.

604
00:31:14.381 --> 00:31:17.738
He didn't know who you were.
- l don't know who you are.

605
00:31:17.842 --> 00:31:21.282
[ Chuckling ] Look. uh...

606
00:31:21.387 --> 00:31:24.789
do you know how hard it is to find
a really good carpenter?

607
00:31:24.893 --> 00:31:25.817
Besides. l think...

608
00:31:25.921 --> 00:31:27.666
he's got a brother
who's a plumber.

609
00:31:27.770 --> 00:31:29.814
Really? A brother
who's a plumber?

610
00:31:29.918 --> 00:31:30.544
l think so.

611
00:31:30.648 --> 00:31:32.871
Do you think l should
sleep with him?

612
00:31:32.975 --> 00:31:34.215
Maybe just this once.

613
00:31:34.319 --> 00:31:38.136
[ Chuckling ]
l think l'm going to start dinner.

614
00:31:38.240 --> 00:31:40.722
The house is gonna be great.

615
00:31:41.985 --> 00:31:44.071
Great.

616
00:31:45.322 --> 00:31:47.226
Great!

617
00:31:47.330 --> 00:31:50.232
Hey. l'm sorry about that--
- Oh. it's all right.

618
00:31:50.336 --> 00:31:51.121
You'll have plenty...

619
00:31:51.225 --> 00:31:52.647
of opportunities to
make it up to us.

620
00:31:52.751 --> 00:31:55.028
You know. usually a woman
calls a carpenter...

621
00:31:55.132 --> 00:31:57.277
she's lookin' for
the old ''hammer and nail.''

622
00:31:57.381 --> 00:31:59.696
And l don't mean--
- Yeah. l know what you mean.

623
00:31:59.800 --> 00:32:02.703
Hey. buddy.
did you really buy this house?

624
00:32:02.807 --> 00:32:04.747
Yes. l did.
- [ Men Snickering ]...

625
00:32:04.851 --> 00:32:06.936
[ Both Laughing ]...

626
00:32:15.310 --> 00:32:18.228
[ Gas Hissing ]

627
00:32:26.238 --> 00:32:28.391
Now.
what was over there?

628
00:32:28.495 --> 00:32:32.397
The stairs. lt began right there
and it curved all the way--...

629
00:32:32.501 --> 00:32:36.409
[ Gas Hissing Continues ]
- [ Both Sniffing ]

630
00:32:37.875 --> 00:32:39.960
Oh. my God!

631
00:32:42.296 --> 00:32:44.744
No. don't!

632
00:32:44.848 --> 00:32:48.659
[ Pilot Light lgnites ]
- What's the matter?

633
00:32:49.803 --> 00:32:52.001
l was just lighting the oven.

634
00:32:52.105 --> 00:32:56.254
Just lighting-- You could've
been killed! We could've all died!

635
00:32:56.359 --> 00:32:58.255
Oh. well.
thank you very much.

636
00:32:58.360 --> 00:33:00.257
l'm not completely helpless
in the kitchen.

637
00:33:00.362 --> 00:33:02.304
l do know how to light an oven.

638
00:33:02.408 --> 00:33:04.886
Well. yeah. but--...

639
00:33:04.990 --> 00:33:08.515
You mean this thing works?
- So far. so good.

640
00:33:08.619 --> 00:33:11.439
Well. it's amazing.
What about the. uh--...

641
00:33:11.544 --> 00:33:13.437
What do you call these?
- The burners.

642
00:33:13.541 --> 00:33:15.284
l haven't tried them yet.

643
00:33:15.388 --> 00:33:17.776
Maybe we shouldn't
press our luck.

644
00:33:17.880 --> 00:33:20.716
Wanna see the refrigerator?
- No.

645
00:33:21.376 --> 00:33:23.990
Water?

646
00:33:24.095 --> 00:33:27.451
[ Grinding. Squeaking ]
- No water.

647
00:33:27.556 --> 00:33:29.384
We've got gas and
electricity. though.

648
00:33:29.489 --> 00:33:30.624
That's two out of three.

649
00:33:30.728 --> 00:33:32.872
Art's calling his brother.
Oh. good news.

650
00:33:32.977 --> 00:33:34.875
You're not gonna have
to sleep with him.

651
00:33:34.980 --> 00:33:38.048
Just a little dinner.
some dancing.

652
00:33:38.153 --> 00:33:40.321
How long do you think
all that'll take?

653
00:33:40.426 --> 00:33:41.468
Two weeks.

654
00:33:41.573 --> 00:33:42.560
Really? That's all?

655
00:33:42.664 --> 00:33:44.471
When do you think
you could start?

656
00:33:44.576 --> 00:33:46.637
Just as soon
as your cheque clears.

657
00:33:46.741 --> 00:33:48.339
Couldn't you at
least hang the door?

658
00:33:48.443 --> 00:33:49.765
l've got enough cash for that.

659
00:33:49.869 --> 00:33:52.145
Haven't got the right materials.

660
00:33:52.249 --> 00:33:55.174
Wood's rotten.
Won't hold a screw.

661
00:33:56.036 --> 00:33:59.028
Which reminds me:

662
00:33:59.132 --> 00:34:02.986
l'm late for my next job.
- [ Engine Starts ]...

663
00:34:03.090 --> 00:34:05.911
lf you know what l mean.
- [ Car Radio ] I gotta be me...

664
00:34:06.015 --> 00:34:09.412
? I gotta be me
- Yeah. l know what you mean.

665
00:34:09.516 --> 00:34:13.208
? What else can I be...

666
00:34:13.554 --> 00:34:16.168
[ Door Opens. Closes ]...

667
00:34:16.272 --> 00:34:19.295
[ Coughing ] In spite of
all the problems...

668
00:34:19.399 --> 00:34:21.026
in spite of the prospect
of indentured...

669
00:34:21.130 --> 00:34:22.551
servitude for the rest of my life...

670
00:34:22.655 --> 00:34:24.927
in debt beyond
my wildest dreams...

671
00:34:25.032 --> 00:34:26.927
l love the house.

672
00:34:27.032 --> 00:34:28.929
So do l.

673
00:34:29.034 --> 00:34:31.119
And l love you.

674
00:34:32.072 --> 00:34:35.156
Life is good.
- ? [ Violin ]...

675
00:34:36.493 --> 00:34:38.397
[ Door Closes ]...

676
00:34:38.501 --> 00:34:41.449
? [ Continues ]...

677
00:34:57.806 --> 00:35:01.336
[ Insects Buzzing ]
- [ Birds Chirping ]...

678
00:35:01.440 --> 00:35:03.525
[ Zipper Zips Down ]...

679
00:35:05.314 --> 00:35:08.398
[ Water Pouring ]

680
00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:15.365
Prostate trouble?

681
00:35:16.909 --> 00:35:20.277
[ Water Stops ]
- [ Zipper Zips Up ]...

682
00:35:37.471 --> 00:35:40.507
[ Birds Chirping Loudly ]...

683
00:35:42.226 --> 00:35:44.130
[ Door Opens ]...

684
00:35:44.234 --> 00:35:46.132
[ Door Closes ]
- [ Footsteps Approaching ]

685
00:35:46.236 --> 00:35:48.428
Well. that was fast.

686
00:35:48.532 --> 00:35:51.432
We have very weak trees.

687
00:35:51.536 --> 00:35:53.975
''Weak trees''?

688
00:35:54.079 --> 00:35:57.268
[ Doorbell Chimes.
Winds Down ]...

689
00:35:57.372 --> 00:35:59.564
l guess that's the door.

690
00:35:59.668 --> 00:36:03.213
Hurry. don't let it ring again.
[ Sighs ]

691
00:36:04.832 --> 00:36:06.736
Wait!

692
00:36:06.840 --> 00:36:08.738
You Fielding?
- Right!

693
00:36:08.842 --> 00:36:10.740
My brother Art recommended you.

694
00:36:10.844 --> 00:36:12.321
l don't usually take
jobs in this area.

695
00:36:12.426 --> 00:36:13.746
l'm glad you can
make an exception.

696
00:36:13.850 --> 00:36:15.871
Let's not get ahead
of ourselves. okay?

697
00:36:15.975 --> 00:36:16.455
l'm sorry.

698
00:36:16.559 --> 00:36:19.460
Where should we start?
- Well. you could offer me a drink.

699
00:36:19.564 --> 00:36:21.459
l don't know
where my manners are.

700
00:36:21.563 --> 00:36:25.640
Here it is. nearly 1 1:30.
You must be parched.

701
00:36:28.897 --> 00:36:30.488
What? Wait a minute!
We haven't even...

702
00:36:30.593 --> 00:36:31.805
talked about the plumbing yet!

703
00:36:31.910 --> 00:36:34.726
And we're not going to.
not with your attitude.

704
00:36:34.830 --> 00:36:37.389
Oh. saving the good scotch
for the company. are we?

705
00:36:37.493 --> 00:36:38.462
No wonder you've
been turned down...

706
00:36:38.566 --> 00:36:39.393
by every plumber in the valley.

707
00:36:39.497 --> 00:36:41.811
That's not true!
- Don't make it worse by lying.

708
00:36:41.915 --> 00:36:45.440
l'm not lying!
l haven't tried everybody yet.

709
00:36:45.544 --> 00:36:47.488
Please.
you gotta help me!

710
00:36:47.592 --> 00:36:50.069
l don't know.

711
00:36:50.174 --> 00:36:51.274
Write me a cheque quick.

712
00:36:51.378 --> 00:36:53.199
before l come to my
senses. Five grand.

713
00:36:53.303 --> 00:36:55.312
Five grand-- Five
thousand dollars?

714
00:36:55.416 --> 00:36:56.660
That's just a deposit.

715
00:36:56.765 --> 00:36:58.662
You didn't even-- Well--...

716
00:36:58.767 --> 00:37:00.942
l'm not tryin' to tell
you your business.

717
00:37:01.046 --> 00:37:03.167
but you haven't even
looked at my pipes.

718
00:37:03.271 --> 00:37:04.665
l looked at them three years ago.

719
00:37:04.770 --> 00:37:06.340
You figure they've
improved with age?

720
00:37:06.444 --> 00:37:08.838
[ Engine Starts ]
- [ Car Radio ] Me...

721
00:37:08.943 --> 00:37:12.345
? I gotta be me...

722
00:37:12.449 --> 00:37:18.479
? What else can I be but what I am

723
00:37:26.288 --> 00:37:28.653
Prep school.
[ Clears Throat ]

724
00:37:28.757 --> 00:37:32.362
Yale.
Phi Beta Kappa.

725
00:37:32.466 --> 00:37:36.285
Four years of law school.
law review.

726
00:37:36.390 --> 00:37:38.535
Are you all right?

727
00:37:38.639 --> 00:37:41.581
Oh. yeah. l'm fine.

728
00:37:41.686 --> 00:37:43.749
The secret is not to.
uh. look down.

729
00:37:43.853 --> 00:37:46.416
Oh. why did you say that?

730
00:37:46.521 --> 00:37:48.715
Look down?
lt's a secret.

731
00:37:48.819 --> 00:37:50.714
l was fine till you said that.

732
00:37:50.819 --> 00:37:52.716
l'm sorry.
You're doin' great.

733
00:37:52.821 --> 00:37:55.685
Mm-hmm.
- Just great.

734
00:38:01.198 --> 00:38:02.241
lf you don't mind.

735
00:38:02.345 --> 00:38:04.311
l'm gonna share this
bath with you...

736
00:38:04.416 --> 00:38:06.271
because l can't do
this a second time.

737
00:38:06.375 --> 00:38:06.524
Ooh!

738
00:38:06.628 --> 00:38:09.110
l think that's a swell idea.

739
00:38:09.128 --> 00:38:13.529
That way you can save your energy
for more worthwhile causes.

740
00:38:13.633 --> 00:38:15.719
Mmm.

741
00:38:17.756 --> 00:38:20.415
Mmm.

742
00:38:20.519 --> 00:38:23.335
Would you get the rest
of the water. okay?

743
00:38:23.439 --> 00:38:25.743
[ Chuckling ]
- [ Sighing ]

744
00:38:26.098 --> 00:38:29.589
Hi. this is Julia Child with a tip
on making crepes Suzette...

745
00:38:29.693 --> 00:38:33.214
that marvellous flaming dessert
that you do at the table.

746
00:38:33.319 --> 00:38:37.598
You need a nice flaming set-up.
I've got a heat source there.

747
00:38:37.702 --> 00:38:39.597
There's an attractive pan.

748
00:38:39.701 --> 00:38:44.294
In the pan I have a mixture
of sugar. butter. orangejuice...

749
00:38:44.398 --> 00:38:46.347
and grated orange peel.

750
00:38:46.451 --> 00:38:47.761
I'm taking a crepe.

751
00:38:47.865 --> 00:38:50.609
and I'm bathing it
in this mixture--...

752
00:38:50.713 --> 00:38:54.347
[ Crackling ]
- [ TV. Child Continues ]...

753
00:38:55.460 --> 00:38:57.868
[ Loud Crackling ]...

754
00:39:03.010 --> 00:39:04.418
[ TV. Child ] I like to use...

755
00:39:04.523 --> 00:39:06.417
a no-stick pan and
heat until water--...

756
00:39:06.522 --> 00:39:10.776
[ Tiles Breaking ]
- [ Electricity Crackling ]...

757
00:39:12.603 --> 00:39:15.006
[ Blender Whirring ]...

758
00:39:15.110 --> 00:39:18.225
[ TV. Child Continues ]...

759
00:39:31.747 --> 00:39:34.611
...and on goes some nice brandy.

760
00:39:34.715 --> 00:39:39.679
Let it bubble up well.
and then dip it into your flames--

761
00:39:44.259 --> 00:39:46.345
Ow!

762
00:40:14.122 --> 00:40:18.199
Little problem in the kitchen.
Nothing trivial.

763
00:40:21.088 --> 00:40:23.286
Well.
the turkey's done.

764
00:40:23.390 --> 00:40:25.702
So is the kitchen.

765
00:40:25.806 --> 00:40:28.914
Actually. it's a little overdone
for my taste.

766
00:40:29.019 --> 00:40:31.377
Let's not go there again.

767
00:40:31.482 --> 00:40:34.381
You don't want to
tell me what happened?

768
00:40:34.486 --> 00:40:35.206
No. l don't.

769
00:40:35.310 --> 00:40:38.617
l just want to relax
in a nice lukewarm bath.

770
00:40:38.721 --> 00:40:40.003
What about this?

771
00:40:40.107 --> 00:40:44.538
[ Walter ] I don't think
that can hurt us any more.

772
00:40:51.869 --> 00:40:54.823
[ Laughing ]...

773
00:41:07.259 --> 00:41:10.176
[ Laughing Hysterically ]

774
00:41:29.740 --> 00:41:32.688
What are you doing?

775
00:41:32.792 --> 00:41:34.983
Save yourself.
- What?

776
00:41:35.087 --> 00:41:36.982
l'm a menace to anything l touch.

777
00:41:37.087 --> 00:41:38.417
The Surgeon General's warning...

778
00:41:38.521 --> 00:41:40.111
should be tattooed
across my forehead.

779
00:41:40.215 --> 00:41:42.906
''Walter Fielding is dangerous
to your health. Don't touch him.''

780
00:41:43.010 --> 00:41:45.829
Save yourself.
- l can't.

781
00:41:45.933 --> 00:41:47.640
l've tried. but l
love Walter Fielding.

782
00:41:47.744 --> 00:41:48.787
No.

783
00:41:48.891 --> 00:41:51.831
l can't give him up.
l'm hopelessly addicted.

784
00:41:51.935 --> 00:41:52.116
No.

785
00:41:52.221 --> 00:41:53.647
You must think of yourself!

786
00:41:53.751 --> 00:41:55.834
l am sinking fast
into the money pit...

787
00:41:55.938 --> 00:41:57.837
and l don't want to
drag you down with me.

788
00:41:57.941 --> 00:42:00.056
Save yourself
while there's still time.

789
00:42:00.160 --> 00:42:01.292
Walter. brighten up.

790
00:42:01.396 --> 00:42:03.135
l hate seeing you like this.

791
00:42:03.239 --> 00:42:05.681
l hate being like
this. l'm a disaster.

792
00:42:05.785 --> 00:42:08.369
These are estimates
from legitimate...

793
00:42:08.473 --> 00:42:10.849
contractors for repairs on the pit.

794
00:42:10.953 --> 00:42:12.811
Those that will actually
come out here...

795
00:42:12.915 --> 00:42:14.727
are so expensive. l
can't talk about it.

796
00:42:14.832 --> 00:42:17.025
Let's not talk about it.

797
00:42:17.129 --> 00:42:19.191
l've just given our last $5.000--...

798
00:42:19.296 --> 00:42:22.780
our last 5.000 borrowed dollars--
to the Shirks.

799
00:42:22.885 --> 00:42:26.573
Walter. l don't mean
to be questioning you. but why--

800
00:42:26.677 --> 00:42:28.576
They were willing to take it!

801
00:42:28.680 --> 00:42:29.786
The legitimate people wanted...

802
00:42:29.891 --> 00:42:31.371
four times as much
just to say ''hello.''

803
00:42:31.475 --> 00:42:33.872
So it's the Shirks.
That's not so bad.

804
00:42:33.976 --> 00:42:35.875
Well. that's if they show up.

805
00:42:35.979 --> 00:42:38.881
Just because they showed up
to collect the money...

806
00:42:38.985 --> 00:42:41.212
is no guarantee that
they'll show up to do the work.

807
00:42:41.317 --> 00:42:44.924
And if they do.
l can't pay for it!

808
00:42:45.029 --> 00:42:48.182
l'm going to help you.
- Do you have a gun?

809
00:42:48.286 --> 00:42:50.002
''Here lies Walter Fielding.

810
00:42:50.107 --> 00:42:52.517
He bought a house.
and it killed him.''

811
00:42:52.622 --> 00:42:54.685
lf l could raise some more money.
would that help?

812
00:42:54.789 --> 00:42:56.736
Depends on how you're gonna
raise the money.

813
00:42:56.840 --> 00:42:57.056
Mmm.

814
00:42:57.161 --> 00:42:59.564
l think l know how.
- l know you know how.

815
00:42:59.668 --> 00:43:03.526
Just stop.
l've got some things l can sell.

816
00:43:03.631 --> 00:43:07.322
l don't wanna talk about money
or the house any more tonight.

817
00:43:07.426 --> 00:43:09.726
Neither do l. We
could just skip town.

818
00:43:09.830 --> 00:43:11.079
borrow some bus fare.

819
00:43:11.183 --> 00:43:15.709
Or we could hitchhike.
hit the open road.

820
00:43:15.814 --> 00:43:17.875
Everything's gonna be just fine.

821
00:43:17.979 --> 00:43:21.381
You'll see. Trust me.
- How?

822
00:43:21.485 --> 00:43:26.094
Don't you trust me?
- lt's not that. lt's just that--

823
00:43:27.357 --> 00:43:30.459
We'll think of somethin'.
Who cares?

824
00:43:40.787 --> 00:43:43.705
[ Engines Rumbling ]...

825
00:44:05.187 --> 00:44:09.618
What's happening?
- Well. stay here. l'll find out.

826
00:44:16.240 --> 00:44:19.194
[ Men Chattering.
Shouting ]

827
00:44:27.417 --> 00:44:31.536
Hi. You must be
Mr Fielding. [ Laughing ]...

828
00:44:31.640 --> 00:44:34.744
Yeah. Yeah. Who--
- l'm from Shirk Brothers.

829
00:44:34.848 --> 00:44:36.637
Your number came up
in the drawing...

830
00:44:36.741 --> 00:44:38.083
this morning. We work today!

831
00:44:38.188 --> 00:44:41.004
Oh. that's great.
That's-- Where is Brad?

832
00:44:41.108 --> 00:44:43.296
Oh. South of France.
l think.

833
00:44:43.400 --> 00:44:45.961
Uh. don't-- Shouldn't he be here?

834
00:44:46.065 --> 00:44:50.007
Brad is the executive plumber.
We do all the work.

835
00:44:50.111 --> 00:44:52.011
We're just about to get started.

836
00:44:52.115 --> 00:44:55.473
You're free to watch if you want.
though l wouldn't recommend it.

837
00:44:55.577 --> 00:44:57.355
Are there any living
things in there?

838
00:44:57.459 --> 00:44:58.396
Well. my girlfr--...

839
00:44:58.501 --> 00:45:02.489
My wife. What the hell.
- Oh. l'd get her out.

840
00:45:02.501 --> 00:45:05.775
Hold it. fellas. Just a second.
There's a woman inside there.

841
00:45:05.879 --> 00:45:07.777
Hold it!
Come on!

842
00:45:07.881 --> 00:45:10.423
Hey. come on! Wait
a minute. fellas.

843
00:45:10.527 --> 00:45:12.493
there's a lady inside there.

844
00:45:12.597 --> 00:45:15.202
H-Here! Here she--

845
00:45:15.306 --> 00:45:19.206
H-Here you go. Okay?
Are you all right?

846
00:45:19.310 --> 00:45:22.250
Yes. thank you.
- ls everything out?

847
00:45:22.355 --> 00:45:25.295
Yeah.
- [ Engine Starts ]...

848
00:45:25.399 --> 00:45:28.550
Okay. Have a nice day!
- Who are they?

849
00:45:28.655 --> 00:45:30.157
The plumbers.
- Are you sure?

850
00:45:30.262 --> 00:45:32.017
No. and l don't care.
l'm just thrilled...

851
00:45:32.122 --> 00:45:33.490
to see somebody actually working.

852
00:45:33.594 --> 00:45:36.764
Mrs Fielding.
don't worry about a thing.

853
00:45:36.868 --> 00:45:39.810
[ Chattering.
Shouting Continues ]...

854
00:45:39.914 --> 00:45:43.323
Okay. guys. let's do it!
- Yeah!

855
00:45:51.168 --> 00:45:53.457
[ Anna ] In our
settlement you listed...

856
00:45:53.561 --> 00:45:55.908
the value of that
painting at $ 1 00.000.

857
00:45:56.012 --> 00:45:57.955
l'll sell it to you for 7 5.

858
00:45:58.059 --> 00:45:59.954
[ Max ] That painting
doesn't interest me.

859
00:46:00.058 --> 00:46:01.956
Yes. it does.
You love that painting.

860
00:46:02.060 --> 00:46:03.958
That's the only reason l took it.

861
00:46:04.062 --> 00:46:05.960
All you want
to talk about is money.

862
00:46:06.064 --> 00:46:07.764
Let's talk about love and sex.

863
00:46:07.868 --> 00:46:10.093
Forget love. let's
just talk about sex.

864
00:46:10.197 --> 00:46:12.340
Max. l'm desperate.
l need money.

865
00:46:12.444 --> 00:46:15.098
l need new plumbing.
l need new appliances.

866
00:46:15.202 --> 00:46:18.805
A new staircase. Max.
- Stop. please. Too boring.

867
00:46:18.909 --> 00:46:22.305
Plastering. landscaping.
painting. a roof.

868
00:46:22.410 --> 00:46:24.389
Too middle class. Stop.

869
00:46:24.493 --> 00:46:28.899
New floors. new tiles.
new fixtures in the bathroom.

870
00:46:29.004 --> 00:46:31.317
Okay. okay. l'll buy it.
l'll give you the money.

871
00:46:31.422 --> 00:46:33.570
Only. please. God.
stop!

872
00:46:33.674 --> 00:46:38.786
Thank you. Max.
Sometimes you can be very sweet.

873
00:46:38.891 --> 00:46:41.080
l know.

874
00:46:41.185 --> 00:46:44.251
How do l look in this?
- Oh. beautiful.

875
00:46:44.355 --> 00:46:48.842
You look beautiful
in everything. Mm-hmm.

876
00:46:49.643 --> 00:46:52.051
Hi!

877
00:46:54.481 --> 00:46:56.385
Hi.

878
00:46:56.489 --> 00:46:58.098
[ Engine Sputters.
Dies ]

879
00:46:58.203 --> 00:47:00.097
What happened?

880
00:47:00.201 --> 00:47:03.103
lt was no picnic. but those boys
are work animals.

881
00:47:03.208 --> 00:47:06.301
Well. everything looks
pretty well under control.

882
00:47:06.406 --> 00:47:06.889
lt does?

883
00:47:06.994 --> 00:47:09.858
Well. not to the layman's eyes.
of course.

884
00:47:09.962 --> 00:47:13.363
They completely ripped up
our house!

885
00:47:13.467 --> 00:47:16.866
They sure as hell did!
They ripped the guts out of it!

886
00:47:16.970 --> 00:47:19.870
They're work animals.
l'm telling you!

887
00:47:19.974 --> 00:47:21.869
Look at those holes!

888
00:47:21.973 --> 00:47:23.871
Then you got your gravel piles...

889
00:47:23.975 --> 00:47:25.873
your sand piles.
your scrap piles.

890
00:47:25.977 --> 00:47:27.875
Animals!
- Animals.

891
00:47:27.979 --> 00:47:31.298
Well. l like a good conversation
as well as anybody. but l gotta run.

892
00:47:31.402 --> 00:47:33.797
Hasta pronto.
if you know what l mean.

893
00:47:33.901 --> 00:47:35.077
Y-You're leaving?

894
00:47:35.181 --> 00:47:37.803
Well. l ain't movin' in. [ Laughing ]

895
00:47:37.907 --> 00:47:40.808
But we'll be back
when you get your permits.

896
00:47:40.912 --> 00:47:43.811
Permits? The permit man
was supposed to be here by 4:00.

897
00:47:43.915 --> 00:47:46.814
Oh. he was. but you or your wife
weren't here to meet him.

898
00:47:46.918 --> 00:47:48.813
We weren't?
Anna's not here?

899
00:47:48.917 --> 00:47:50.815
No. no.
l would've noticed.

900
00:47:50.919 --> 00:47:52.817
The permit man
was pretty agitated.

901
00:47:52.921 --> 00:47:54.819
Really steamed his clams.

902
00:47:54.923 --> 00:47:56.264
Said he'd be back...

903
00:47:56.368 --> 00:47:58.824
when you grow udders
and get milked.

904
00:47:58.928 --> 00:48:00.825
[ Laughs ]
- That's a long time.

905
00:48:00.929 --> 00:48:02.827
Yeah. Yeah.

906
00:48:02.931 --> 00:48:04.688
Well. if he ever does come back.

907
00:48:04.792 --> 00:48:06.832
you call me and
we'll finish the job.

908
00:48:06.936 --> 00:48:10.004
When l do get the permits.
how long will the job take?

909
00:48:10.108 --> 00:48:12.002
Two weeks.

910
00:48:12.107 --> 00:48:14.004
Two weeks?
Two weeks?

911
00:48:14.109 --> 00:48:15.604
You sound like a parakeet.

912
00:48:15.708 --> 00:48:17.799
''Two weeks? Two
weeks?'' [ Laughs ]

913
00:48:17.903 --> 00:48:20.928
Well. uh. two weeks.
lt's-- lt's amazing.

914
00:48:21.032 --> 00:48:22.930
Amazing. nothing.
- [ Engine Starts ]...

915
00:48:23.034 --> 00:48:27.643
lt'll be a regular miracle.
[ Continues Laughing ]...

916
00:48:28.200 --> 00:48:31.117
[ Phone Ringing ]...

917
00:48:33.539 --> 00:48:36.729
[ Ringing Continues ]
- [ Groans ]...

918
00:48:39.002 --> 00:48:41.088
[ Groans ]...

919
00:48:43.048 --> 00:48:45.956
[ Ringing Continues ]

920
00:48:46.060 --> 00:48:47.955
Hello?

921
00:48:48.059 --> 00:48:50.206
Oh. hi there.

922
00:48:50.311 --> 00:48:52.709
''Tone''?
My voice has no tone.

923
00:48:52.813 --> 00:48:55.716
Because l'm standing
in a pile of rubble...

924
00:48:55.820 --> 00:48:58.214
and we don't
have the permits to un-rubble it.

925
00:48:58.319 --> 00:49:00.366
''Exaggerating''?
Honey. we're living...

926
00:49:00.471 --> 00:49:01.888
in Swiss cheese with a door.

927
00:49:01.992 --> 00:49:05.142
''Mozart''? Mozart is dead.
His troubles are over.

928
00:49:05.246 --> 00:49:07.141
Help me!

929
00:49:07.245 --> 00:49:10.147
[ Sighs ] All right. l'm sorry.

930
00:49:10.251 --> 00:49:14.277
You're right. lf you had to work.
you had to work.

931
00:49:14.381 --> 00:49:16.275
Oh. l-l-l love you too.

932
00:49:16.379 --> 00:49:19.531
Where is the guy's number?
The permit man.

933
00:49:19.636 --> 00:49:21.530
ln the den. you think.

934
00:49:21.635 --> 00:49:24.032
l will pick you up at the station.

935
00:49:24.136 --> 00:49:25.941
Just give me a call...

936
00:49:26.045 --> 00:49:29.679
when you get there.
[ Kissing Sounds ]...

937
00:49:40.522 --> 00:49:42.608
''Shrapp''?

938
00:49:54.786 --> 00:49:57.190
ls Mr Shrapp in?

939
00:49:57.294 --> 00:50:00.197
Mr Shrapp.
Walter Fielding.

940
00:50:00.301 --> 00:50:03.200
Hey. watch what you say
about my mother. now.

941
00:50:03.304 --> 00:50:05.410
Mr Shrapp.
let's be adults about this.

942
00:50:05.514 --> 00:50:08.747
l'm-- Look. l'm very sorry
l wasn't here this afternoon.

943
00:50:08.852 --> 00:50:12.372
My wife was poisoned
and taken to the hospital.

944
00:50:12.476 --> 00:50:14.375
[ Taps Foot ]

945
00:50:14.479 --> 00:50:17.381
Well. what would
cut any ice with you?

946
00:50:17.485 --> 00:50:21.739
A bribe? Sure.
Can you be here in a half an hour?

947
00:50:21.814 --> 00:50:23.717
All right.

948
00:50:23.822 --> 00:50:25.720
Cash? No problem.

949
00:50:25.824 --> 00:50:27.940
[ Dial Tone ]

950
00:50:28.237 --> 00:50:29.935
Weasel.

951
00:50:30.039 --> 00:50:32.984
Cash.
Cash. cash. ca--...

952
00:50:38.372 --> 00:50:40.457
[ Grunts ]...

953
00:50:41.667 --> 00:50:44.326
[ Continues Grunting ] H-Help!

954
00:50:54.304 --> 00:50:57.252
[ Walter ]? Come on. everybody...

955
00:50:57.356 --> 00:51:00.257
? I said let's play a game...

956
00:51:00.361 --> 00:51:03.427
? I bet ya I can make a rhyme...

957
00:51:03.531 --> 00:51:05.925
? Out of anybody's name?

958
00:51:06.030 --> 00:51:07.928
Anna!
? Anna-Anna. bo-banna?

959
00:51:08.033 --> 00:51:09.764
? Banana-fanna. fo-fanna?

960
00:51:09.868 --> 00:51:12.143
? Fee-fi. mo-manna?

961
00:51:12.247 --> 00:51:14.104
? Anna?

962
00:51:14.209 --> 00:51:15.981
Let's try Brad!

963
00:51:16.085 --> 00:51:18.147
? Brad. Brad. bo-rad
Banana-fanna?

964
00:51:18.251 --> 00:51:20.149
[ Knocks ]
- [ Walter ] Walter!

965
00:51:20.253 --> 00:51:21.832
Fielding!
- ? Walter. Walter. bo-balter

966
00:51:21.936 --> 00:51:22.937
Banana-fanna. fo-falter...

967
00:51:23.041 --> 00:51:25.989
? Fee-fi. mo-malter Walter??

968
00:51:26.093 --> 00:51:28.994
[ Knocking Continues ]
- Hello-- [ Grunts ]

969
00:51:29.099 --> 00:51:31.184
Hello!
Hello! l'm here!

970
00:51:31.264 --> 00:51:33.162
Are you in there.
Fielding?

971
00:51:33.266 --> 00:51:35.164
[ Continues Knocking ]

972
00:51:35.268 --> 00:51:38.170
Y-Yeah!
l-l'm here.

973
00:51:38.274 --> 00:51:40.169
M-My chest is constricted.

974
00:51:40.273 --> 00:51:43.963
l can't shout.
O-Oww! Oww!

975
00:51:44.068 --> 00:51:45.966
[ Walter Groaning ]

976
00:51:46.071 --> 00:51:47.161
Okay. Fielding.

977
00:51:47.266 --> 00:51:50.183
l can hear you in
there laughing at me.

978
00:51:50.287 --> 00:51:52.680
This is it.
you duck fart!

979
00:51:52.785 --> 00:51:55.053
l'm leaving. and l'm
never coming back!

980
00:51:55.157 --> 00:51:56.354
Ya hear me. Fielding?

981
00:51:56.458 --> 00:51:59.692
Y-Y-Yes. l hear you!

982
00:51:59.796 --> 00:52:02.317
I'm tearing up your permit!

983
00:52:02.421 --> 00:52:04.318
There!

984
00:52:04.422 --> 00:52:07.436
Nobody laughs
at Montgomery Shrapp!

985
00:52:09.213 --> 00:52:12.628
[ Phone Ringing ]...

986
00:52:15.135 --> 00:52:17.591
[ Ringing Continues ]...

987
00:53:04.810 --> 00:53:06.714
[ Brakes Compress ]...

988
00:53:06.818 --> 00:53:09.760
[ Anna ] Good Lord!

989
00:53:09.864 --> 00:53:13.015
You testin' missiles here.
or what?

990
00:53:13.119 --> 00:53:15.601
The house is gonna be great.

991
00:53:16.780 --> 00:53:21.187
[ Truck Engine Idling.
Horn Blasting ]...

992
00:53:21.291 --> 00:53:24.925
[ Brakes Decompress.
Truck Pulls Away ]...

993
00:53:31.712 --> 00:53:33.616
[ Footsteps ]...

994
00:53:33.720 --> 00:53:36.911
[ Keys Jingling.
Lock Unlocking ]

995
00:53:37.015 --> 00:53:38.906
Shh.

996
00:53:39.011 --> 00:53:41.096
[ Door Closes ]

997
00:53:42.681 --> 00:53:45.302
Oh. my God.

998
00:53:47.352 --> 00:53:49.301
Walter!

999
00:53:49.405 --> 00:53:51.491
Oh!
Oh. A-Anna!

1000
00:53:51.532 --> 00:53:54.931
Thank God it's you!
Thank God! Ohh!

1001
00:53:55.035 --> 00:53:56.931
Walter?

1002
00:53:57.035 --> 00:54:00.436
Thank God you're here. honey!
- ls that you?

1003
00:54:00.541 --> 00:54:02.769
[ Laughs ] ls it me?

1004
00:54:02.873 --> 00:54:05.975
Ha! ls it me?
[ Continues Laughing ]

1005
00:54:08.707 --> 00:54:12.115
Anna. I've been here so long
I'm hallucinating.

1006
00:54:12.219 --> 00:54:15.286
A while ago I thought
the Care Bears were here.

1007
00:54:15.390 --> 00:54:17.284
Walter?

1008
00:54:17.389 --> 00:54:19.639
Farm animals. or geese
and chickens--...

1009
00:54:19.743 --> 00:54:20.957
[ Continues Laughing ]

1010
00:54:21.061 --> 00:54:22.957
Walter?

1011
00:54:23.061 --> 00:54:25.004
Upstairs!

1012
00:54:25.108 --> 00:54:27.002
Are you all right?

1013
00:54:27.107 --> 00:54:30.801
No. l'm not all right.
Not at all.

1014
00:54:32.523 --> 00:54:34.427
No!

1015
00:54:34.531 --> 00:54:36.928
Where are you?
- l'm in the den.

1016
00:54:37.032 --> 00:54:39.935
No. you're not.
I was just in there.

1017
00:54:40.039 --> 00:54:43.227
l'm in the den. l swear it.
Please believe me.

1018
00:54:43.331 --> 00:54:46.483
Will you stop fooling around.
Walter? I'm tired.

1019
00:54:46.588 --> 00:54:48.482
l'm right here.

1020
00:54:48.587 --> 00:54:50.900
Look. Walter.
enough is enough.

1021
00:54:51.005 --> 00:54:53.241
l'm right here!

1022
00:54:54.920 --> 00:54:57.035
Where?

1023
00:54:57.139 --> 00:54:59.798
ln the floor.
behind the chair.

1024
00:55:03.095 --> 00:55:05.764
[ Laughing ] Ohh!

1025
00:55:08.392 --> 00:55:10.628
Oh. laughing.
[ Chuckles ]...

1026
00:55:10.733 --> 00:55:14.189
[ Laughing Continues ]
- We're laughing.

1027
00:55:14.273 --> 00:55:16.177
The permit man was here.

1028
00:55:16.281 --> 00:55:18.345
Oh. that's good.
- No. it's not.

1029
00:55:18.450 --> 00:55:22.140
Now tomorrow l've got to
take off work. drive to his office...

1030
00:55:22.244 --> 00:55:24.143
and kiss his ass.

1031
00:55:24.247 --> 00:55:26.333
Oh!
- [ Thud ]...

1032
00:55:31.081 --> 00:55:33.887
[ Wind Gusting ]
- Well. thanks to that fall...

1033
00:55:33.991 --> 00:55:35.857
we're now the same height.

1034
00:55:35.961 --> 00:55:37.865
Yeah. that's much better.

1035
00:55:37.969 --> 00:55:39.867
[ Wind Gusting ]...

1036
00:55:39.971 --> 00:55:42.873
So. why did rehearsal run so long?
- That was my fault.

1037
00:55:42.977 --> 00:55:45.501
We got off to a late
start because l was...

1038
00:55:45.605 --> 00:55:47.708
haggling with Max
over the painting.

1039
00:55:47.812 --> 00:55:50.670
How. exactly. would you
define ''haggling''?

1040
00:55:50.775 --> 00:55:54.509
What do you mean by that?
- l thought that was my question.

1041
00:55:54.613 --> 00:55:56.698
Are you jealous of Max?

1042
00:55:58.150 --> 00:56:00.235
Jealous of Max?

1043
00:56:00.325 --> 00:56:02.223
Don't be silly.

1044
00:56:02.327 --> 00:56:05.229
Just because he's rich. famous.
good-looking. brilliant.

1045
00:56:05.333 --> 00:56:08.072
l mean. what's he got
that l haven't got?

1046
00:56:08.177 --> 00:56:08.556
Walls.

1047
00:56:08.660 --> 00:56:10.746
l feel much better.

1048
00:56:23.509 --> 00:56:25.594
Good night. hon.

1049
00:56:30.307 --> 00:56:32.392
Good night.

1050
00:56:36.897 --> 00:56:39.723
[ Shouting. Chattering ]

1051
00:56:39.827 --> 00:56:43.890
Look out for that thing.
You're gonna fall off of it.

1052
00:56:43.995 --> 00:56:47.097
[ Shouting.
Chattering Continue ]...

1053
00:56:50.869 --> 00:56:53.612
[ Moaning ]...

1054
00:56:53.716 --> 00:56:57.172
[ Kissing Sounds.
Moaning Continues ]...

1055
00:57:01.380 --> 00:57:05.582
[ Continues Moaning ]

1056
00:57:05.686 --> 00:57:07.413
Get to work!

1057
00:57:07.517 --> 00:57:09.918
[ Anna Screaming ]

1058
00:57:14.852 --> 00:57:17.760
Four months
since I got those permits.

1059
00:57:17.864 --> 00:57:19.016
They're not even half done.

1060
00:57:19.120 --> 00:57:20.763
They said two weeks
for the whole job.

1061
00:57:20.867 --> 00:57:23.766
You're telling me this
like l haven't been here.

1062
00:57:23.870 --> 00:57:25.765
We're going through a rough time.

1063
00:57:25.869 --> 00:57:28.903
Let's remember not to
take it out on each other.

1064
00:57:29.007 --> 00:57:29.762
You're right.

1065
00:57:29.867 --> 00:57:31.871
You hear about that
guy up in the Bronx.

1066
00:57:31.975 --> 00:57:33.774
went crazy. thought
he was a pigeon?

1067
00:57:33.878 --> 00:57:36.779
They found him in the park
throwing bread crumbs at himself.

1068
00:57:36.883 --> 00:57:39.360
He was just putting in
a guest bathroom.

1069
00:57:39.465 --> 00:57:39.772
Okay.

1070
00:57:39.877 --> 00:57:43.284
So let's be nice to each other.
We're all we've got.

1071
00:57:43.388 --> 00:57:45.284
Don't forget to get the water.

1072
00:57:45.388 --> 00:57:47.915
Haven't l gotten the water
every morning for four months?

1073
00:57:48.019 --> 00:57:48.281
Walter.

1074
00:57:48.385 --> 00:57:49.507
Do l ever forget the water?

1075
00:57:49.611 --> 00:57:51.211
Don't do this. Walter.
Walter. Walter!

1076
00:57:51.315 --> 00:57:53.401
l'm sorry.

1077
00:57:54.475 --> 00:57:56.690
The bucket's in the hall.

1078
00:57:57.811 --> 00:57:59.842
[ Muttering ]
l know where the bucket is.

1079
00:57:59.947 --> 00:58:03.935
You don't have to tell me
where the bucket is.

1080
00:58:13.994 --> 00:58:16.397
Stairs!
Ha!

1081
00:58:16.502 --> 00:58:19.405
A staircase!
We have stairs!

1082
00:58:19.509 --> 00:58:21.594
[ Laughing ]

1083
00:58:23.337 --> 00:58:27.631
Oh. hello. Mr Stairs.
l've missed you.

1084
00:58:29.635 --> 00:58:31.833
Anna?
Anna. darling!

1085
00:58:31.937 --> 00:58:33.833
Did you get the water?

1086
00:58:33.937 --> 00:58:36.022
We have stairs!

1087
00:58:36.106 --> 00:58:39.208
[ Laughing ] lt's happening. honey.

1088
00:58:39.279 --> 00:58:41.173
Everything's gonna be fixed.

1089
00:58:41.278 --> 00:58:43.885
[ Sobbing ] We have stairs.

1090
00:58:43.990 --> 00:58:46.097
That's terrific.

1091
00:58:46.201 --> 00:58:49.569
Everything's gonna be wonderful.
- Yes.

1092
00:58:49.622 --> 00:58:52.016
Sweetheart.
I could really use some water.

1093
00:58:52.121 --> 00:58:55.200
[ Sniffling ] Yeah. Right away.

1094
00:58:59.456 --> 00:59:01.360
S-Say. Curly?

1095
00:59:01.464 --> 00:59:04.366
Yo!
- Could you send up some water?

1096
00:59:04.471 --> 00:59:07.742
We're a little busy today. Walter.
tryin' to build a house.

1097
00:59:07.846 --> 00:59:10.748
l'll get it myself.
l'll use my new stairs.

1098
00:59:10.852 --> 00:59:12.747
That's my boy.

1099
00:59:12.851 --> 00:59:15.252
Tar bucket comin' down.

1100
00:59:20.853 --> 00:59:23.256
Morning. James.
- Morning!

1101
00:59:23.360 --> 00:59:25.720
Alka-Seltzer.
- Just a minute.

1102
00:59:25.824 --> 00:59:28.724
Any idea when you're going
to be finished here?

1103
00:59:28.828 --> 00:59:30.723
Two weeks.
- That's what l thought.

1104
00:59:30.827 --> 00:59:32.770
Alka-Seltzer.
Here you go.

1105
00:59:32.874 --> 00:59:37.390
Oh. You know you're almost out
of birth control pills?

1106
00:59:37.494 --> 00:59:39.580
Thank you. James.

1107
00:59:39.669 --> 00:59:42.111
Walter.
Walter!

1108
00:59:42.216 --> 00:59:45.161
The water! l know.
l'm getting it.

1109
00:59:46.712 --> 00:59:48.928
[ Whistles ] Hey. Walter!

1110
00:59:49.014 --> 00:59:52.081
You want this room painted blue.
like in the hallway?

1111
00:59:52.185 --> 00:59:53.876
No. l do not. That's all wood--

1112
00:59:53.980 --> 00:59:56.121
What do you mean.
''like the hallway''?

1113
00:59:56.225 --> 00:59:58.125
The hallway.
Blue. right?

1114
00:59:58.230 --> 00:59:59.922
l want nothing blue.
Nothing!

1115
01:00:00.026 --> 01:00:03.675
Oh. man. Now l gotta go flush out
my paint sprayer.

1116
01:00:03.779 --> 01:00:05.303
Oh. that's a bummer.

1117
01:00:05.408 --> 01:00:09.010
? [ Radio. Opera ]
- Have you seen Mr Fielding?

1118
01:00:09.114 --> 01:00:11.013
Fielding?
- Yeah.

1119
01:00:11.117 --> 01:00:13.680
Don't know any Fieldings
around here. ln Cincinnati--

1120
01:00:13.785 --> 01:00:15.870
Walter?

1121
01:00:15.872 --> 01:00:18.525
Oh. Walter!
Yeah. Walter.

1122
01:00:18.629 --> 01:00:21.899
He was supposed to bring me
a bucket of water.

1123
01:00:22.003 --> 01:00:24.317
Bring you some water?
- Yeah. Do-- No--...

1124
01:00:24.421 --> 01:00:26.320
Ohh! Ohh!
- How's that?

1125
01:00:26.424 --> 01:00:29.160
[ Laughs ] lt's a miracle.

1126
01:00:29.265 --> 01:00:32.670
[ Continues Laughing ] Yeah!

1127
01:00:33.133 --> 01:00:34.666
?? [ Ranchero ]

1128
01:00:34.770 --> 01:00:36.856
Walter.

1129
01:00:38.263 --> 01:00:41.422
l wanna ask you something.
You're a lawyer. right?

1130
01:00:41.526 --> 01:00:41.829
Yeah.

1131
01:00:41.934 --> 01:00:45.175
Last year my father
was hit in the head by a golf ball.

1132
01:00:45.280 --> 01:00:48.470
? [ Radio. Pop ]
- Oh. can l unplug--

1133
01:00:48.488 --> 01:00:50.053
Now. he seemed okay...

1134
01:00:50.157 --> 01:00:52.554
but last week
we were watching TV...

1135
01:00:52.658 --> 01:00:56.099
and l put on the Bob Hope
Desert Classic from Palm Springs.

1136
01:00:56.203 --> 01:00:58.102
He goes friggin' nuts!

1137
01:00:58.206 --> 01:01:00.104
My father. not Bob Hope.

1138
01:01:00.208 --> 01:01:03.527
So he kicks in
the friggin' TV screen. Now--...

1139
01:01:03.631 --> 01:01:06.113
? [ Pop Continues ]...

1140
01:01:10.254 --> 01:01:12.152
l'd have to study it.
but l'd say you got...

1141
01:01:12.257 --> 01:01:13.534
a great case against Bob Hope.

1142
01:01:13.638 --> 01:01:15.724
Thanks. man.

1143
01:01:21.974 --> 01:01:24.059
[ Saw Buzzing ]

1144
01:01:28.105 --> 01:01:30.190
Aaah!

1145
01:01:33.694 --> 01:01:36.149
? [ Opera Continues ]...

1146
01:01:45.831 --> 01:01:48.286
?? [ Bluegrass ]...

1147
01:01:54.047 --> 01:01:56.133
?? [ Continues ]...

1148
01:01:59.219 --> 01:02:02.173
?? [ Opera ]...

1149
01:02:13.859 --> 01:02:16.528
? [ Opera Continues ]...

1150
01:02:35.589 --> 01:02:38.127
[ Shouting. Screaming ]...

1151
01:02:54.399 --> 01:02:56.725
? [ Opera Continues ]...

1152
01:03:27.432 --> 01:03:30.054
? [ Opera. Finale ]...

1153
01:03:35.274 --> 01:03:38.515
That was not so bad.
- [ Musicians Laughing ]...

1154
01:03:38.620 --> 01:03:41.065
[ Man ] Are you
happy with that one?

1155
01:03:41.169 --> 01:03:42.851
l am not unhappy with it.

1156
01:03:42.955 --> 01:03:45.165
It's the best that
miserable symphony...

1157
01:03:45.269 --> 01:03:46.312
has ever sounded.

1158
01:03:46.416 --> 01:03:50.190
You have my congratulations.
and you may go home.

1159
01:03:50.294 --> 01:03:51.451
[ Murmuring. Chattering ]

1160
01:03:51.556 --> 01:03:53.197
But don't you want to hear it back?

1161
01:03:53.301 --> 01:03:56.699
No. if there's something wrong
with it it's your fault...

1162
01:03:56.804 --> 01:03:59.326
and you will hang for it.

1163
01:03:59.430 --> 01:04:01.327
Do you have a cigarette?

1164
01:04:01.431 --> 01:04:03.516
l'm sorry.

1165
01:04:10.976 --> 01:04:12.880
lt was beautiful.
Max.

1166
01:04:12.984 --> 01:04:15.049
Better than Szell's version?

1167
01:04:15.153 --> 01:04:17.191
Mmm. l wondered
why you did this.

1168
01:04:17.295 --> 01:04:18.888
l know you never liked it.

1169
01:04:18.992 --> 01:04:21.387
Well?

1170
01:04:21.492 --> 01:04:23.890
lt was better.
- Thank you.

1171
01:04:23.994 --> 01:04:26.897
lt's a pity
that son of a bitch isn't alive...

1172
01:04:27.001 --> 01:04:29.900
because it would kill him
to hear that.

1173
01:04:30.004 --> 01:04:31.899
Have you got a cigarette?

1174
01:04:32.003 --> 01:04:33.901
You stopped smoking
five years ago.

1175
01:04:34.005 --> 01:04:35.903
l started again two weeks ago.

1176
01:04:36.007 --> 01:04:38.404
Can l have the damn cigarette?

1177
01:04:38.509 --> 01:04:40.594
Mmm.
Filters.

1178
01:04:46.178 --> 01:04:49.004
You seem a little tense.

1179
01:04:49.108 --> 01:04:52.006
Your shoulders are up
over your ears.

1180
01:04:52.110 --> 01:04:55.297
Are you all right?
- Don't l look all right?

1181
01:04:55.402 --> 01:04:57.299
ln a word. no.

1182
01:04:57.404 --> 01:04:59.048
The only good part of our divorce...

1183
01:04:59.152 --> 01:05:00.844
was that it seemed
to make you happy.

1184
01:05:00.948 --> 01:05:04.101
For you to be without me
and unhappy...

1185
01:05:04.205 --> 01:05:06.100
is such a waste.

1186
01:05:06.204 --> 01:05:09.440
You are making me sad.

1187
01:05:09.544 --> 01:05:11.649
Walter's in Philadelphia...

1188
01:05:11.753 --> 01:05:15.864
and the idea of going back
to that house. alone--

1189
01:05:15.968 --> 01:05:18.361
Oh. God.

1190
01:05:18.465 --> 01:05:22.285
Why don't we have dinner
and a huge amount of alcohol?

1191
01:05:22.389 --> 01:05:24.950
l'm not dressed for a restaurant.

1192
01:05:25.054 --> 01:05:28.957
My place.
Our old place.

1193
01:05:29.061 --> 01:05:31.962
You can have a hot bath.
- [ Sighs ]

1194
01:05:32.066 --> 01:05:36.092
We'll have a fire. Hwang will make
anything you want for dinner.

1195
01:05:36.197 --> 01:05:38.135
Duck l'orange.
- [ Chuckles ]

1196
01:05:38.239 --> 01:05:40.383
Twelve-year-old scotch.

1197
01:05:40.487 --> 01:05:42.386
ln clean glasses.

1198
01:05:42.490 --> 01:05:44.576
That can be arranged.

1199
01:05:44.576 --> 01:05:46.474
l'm not going to bed with you.

1200
01:05:46.578 --> 01:05:48.663
l may not ask you.

1201
01:06:06.758 --> 01:06:08.844
[ Sighs ]

1202
01:06:12.598 --> 01:06:14.502
Oh. my God.

1203
01:06:14.606 --> 01:06:16.504
Good morning.

1204
01:06:16.608 --> 01:06:18.716
Oh. my God.
- What's wrong?

1205
01:06:18.821 --> 01:06:21.720
What happened?
What did we do?

1206
01:06:21.825 --> 01:06:24.723
What have we done? Oh. my God!
- Calm down.

1207
01:06:24.828 --> 01:06:27.132
You were a little looped.
You sang a few songs.

1208
01:06:27.236 --> 01:06:27.842
The Beatles?

1209
01:06:27.946 --> 01:06:30.266
The entire catalogue.
- What else?

1210
01:06:30.371 --> 01:06:33.274
You don't remember?
- lt was duck for dinner. Right?

1211
01:06:33.378 --> 01:06:34.568
Followed by crepe Suzettes.

1212
01:06:34.672 --> 01:06:36.277
l don't remember
the crepe Suzettes.

1213
01:06:36.381 --> 01:06:38.275
You don't remember the piano?
- No.

1214
01:06:38.380 --> 01:06:40.777
Under the piano?
- l don't wanna hear any more.

1215
01:06:40.881 --> 01:06:42.784
lt was incredible.
Better than Zurich.

1216
01:06:42.888 --> 01:06:43.196
Zurich?

1217
01:06:43.300 --> 01:06:45.772
The police came.
You don't remember any of this?

1218
01:06:45.877 --> 01:06:46.194
Oh. no.

1219
01:06:46.298 --> 01:06:48.202
My shoe!

1220
01:06:48.306 --> 01:06:50.375
Not my shoe!
- Last night you were...

1221
01:06:50.479 --> 01:06:51.866
the animal l remember.

1222
01:06:51.970 --> 01:06:52.762
I don't need shoes!

1223
01:06:52.866 --> 01:06:54.325
Come back to me. and the police...

1224
01:06:54.429 --> 01:06:55.370
will come every night.

1225
01:06:55.474 --> 01:06:57.378
l love you.
- This is a nightmare.

1226
01:06:57.482 --> 01:06:59.380
Last night you said you loved me...

1227
01:06:59.484 --> 01:07:02.386
that we would be together
the rest of our lives.

1228
01:07:02.490 --> 01:07:04.385
I wasn't drunk.
I was insane!

1229
01:07:04.489 --> 01:07:06.387
When are you going to tell Walter?
- Never!

1230
01:07:06.491 --> 01:07:09.099
You're just going to walk out
on him without saying anything?

1231
01:07:09.203 --> 01:07:10.385
I am not walking out on him.

1232
01:07:10.489 --> 01:07:12.892
l am in love with him.
Not you. him.

1233
01:07:12.997 --> 01:07:14.799
No. this whole
wonderful realization...

1234
01:07:14.904 --> 01:07:15.661
has confused you.

1235
01:07:15.765 --> 01:07:15.890
Oh!

1236
01:07:15.994 --> 01:07:18.608
Talk this over with Walter.
and you'll see.

1237
01:07:18.713 --> 01:07:21.614
Lying.
- What?

1238
01:07:21.718 --> 01:07:24.617
I'm going to have to do
a lot of lying.

1239
01:07:24.721 --> 01:07:27.620
No. Tell him the truth.
- l'll lose him.

1240
01:07:27.724 --> 01:07:31.092
Hey. take a chance.
- [ Door Slams ]...

1241
01:07:32.261 --> 01:07:33.998
[ Man ]
? Bump-bump-ba-bump-bump?

1242
01:07:34.102 --> 01:07:35.916
[ Children ]
? Bump-bump-ba-bump-bump?

1243
01:07:36.021 --> 01:07:37.586
[ Man ]? Bump-bump-bump?

1244
01:07:37.690 --> 01:07:39.381
[ Children ]? Bump-bump-bump?

1245
01:07:39.486 --> 01:07:41.130
[ Man ]
? Bump-bump-ba-bump-bump?

1246
01:07:41.234 --> 01:07:43.093
[ Children ]
? Bump-bump-ba-bump-bump?

1247
01:07:43.198 --> 01:07:44.760
[ Man ]? Bump-bump-bump?

1248
01:07:44.864 --> 01:07:46.594
[ Children ]? Bump-bump-bump?

1249
01:07:46.698 --> 01:07:48.345
[ Man ]
? Bump-bump-ba-bump-bump?

1250
01:07:48.450 --> 01:07:49.976
[ Children ]
? Bump-bump-ba-bump-bump?

1251
01:07:50.081 --> 01:07:51.974
?? [ Continues ]
- You'd better let me off here.

1252
01:07:52.078 --> 01:07:53.833
l don't think you can
make it up the driveway.

1253
01:07:53.938 --> 01:07:54.971
They testin' missiles here?

1254
01:07:55.075 --> 01:07:56.295
That's right. buddy. we are.

1255
01:07:56.399 --> 01:07:57.983
and it's very
hush-hush. Top secret.

1256
01:07:58.087 --> 01:08:01.320
So forget you were up here
and forget you saw any of this.

1257
01:08:01.424 --> 01:08:04.138
And forget about a tip.
- [ Man. Children On Tape ]...

1258
01:08:04.243 --> 01:08:05.023
? l am a pizza?

1259
01:08:05.127 --> 01:08:08.740
? Ready to munch?
- Ah. home. crap home.

1260
01:08:08.844 --> 01:08:11.408
? I am a pizza
- ? I am a pi--...

1261
01:08:11.512 --> 01:08:13.508
l still can't get used to the idea of...

1262
01:08:13.612 --> 01:08:15.454
having hot water
whenever we want it.

1263
01:08:15.558 --> 01:08:18.123
Yeah.
Yeah.

1264
01:08:18.227 --> 01:08:21.131
So. what'd you do last night?
- Oh. nothing much.

1265
01:08:21.236 --> 01:08:23.130
Where'd you eat?

1266
01:08:23.235 --> 01:08:25.132
What?

1267
01:08:25.237 --> 01:08:27.134
Last night.
Where did you eat?

1268
01:08:27.239 --> 01:08:29.846
Oh.
The Four Seasons.

1269
01:08:29.951 --> 01:08:32.308
Well. l'm glad it wasn't
anything special.

1270
01:08:32.412 --> 01:08:34.308
Actually.
it was a little special.

1271
01:08:34.412 --> 01:08:36.810
We had just done probably
the finest performance...

1272
01:08:36.914 --> 01:08:38.979
of Haydn's
Surprise Symphony ever.

1273
01:08:39.084 --> 01:08:40.981
Really.

1274
01:08:41.086 --> 01:08:43.361
Uh. please tell me you didn't pay.

1275
01:08:43.465 --> 01:08:45.361
l didn't.

1276
01:08:45.465 --> 01:08:47.824
Max took us.

1277
01:08:47.928 --> 01:08:50.333
Well. that must have been
some performance.

1278
01:08:50.438 --> 01:08:50.735
It was.

1279
01:08:50.839 --> 01:08:55.323
It's never been my favourite piece
of music. but we really did it well.

1280
01:08:55.427 --> 01:08:57.164
How was Max?

1281
01:08:57.269 --> 01:08:59.166
Fine!

1282
01:08:59.271 --> 01:09:02.816
l mean. he was very pleased
with himself.

1283
01:09:03.602 --> 01:09:05.506
He asked after you.

1284
01:09:05.610 --> 01:09:08.007
Oh. that's-- that's very nice.
- Mm-hmm.

1285
01:09:08.112 --> 01:09:10.510
Did you sleep with him?

1286
01:09:10.614 --> 01:09:12.513
l hope you don't mind.

1287
01:09:12.617 --> 01:09:16.611
Of course. we can't go back
to the Four Seasons again.

1288
01:09:16.715 --> 01:09:17.929
[ Walter Laughs ]

1289
01:09:18.033 --> 01:09:19.937
Did you?

1290
01:09:20.041 --> 01:09:21.939
Walter!

1291
01:09:22.043 --> 01:09:24.190
Did you?

1292
01:09:24.295 --> 01:09:26.071
Are you serious?

1293
01:09:26.176 --> 01:09:29.074
Well. l know you weren't here
last night...

1294
01:09:29.179 --> 01:09:32.077
because l called.
and. uh. guess what.

1295
01:09:32.182 --> 01:09:34.409
l don't know.
You tell me.

1296
01:09:34.513 --> 01:09:36.412
[ Plate Slams On Table ]
- No answer.

1297
01:09:36.516 --> 01:09:39.264
[ Sawing Violently Into Bread ]

1298
01:09:40.806 --> 01:09:44.048
Walter. do you want to tell me
what you're saying?

1299
01:09:44.152 --> 01:09:46.379
l'm not saying anything.

1300
01:09:46.483 --> 01:09:49.637
Actually.
what I'm saying is...

1301
01:09:49.741 --> 01:09:50.831
that I would hope that if...

1302
01:09:50.936 --> 01:09:52.640
there was something
for you to tell me--...

1303
01:09:52.744 --> 01:09:55.019
for example. that you'd
spent last night...

1304
01:09:55.123 --> 01:09:57.019
with Max-- that you would tell me...

1305
01:09:57.123 --> 01:10:00.521
that it would be okay
for you to tell me.

1306
01:10:00.626 --> 01:10:04.275
You're just going
to have to trust me.

1307
01:10:04.379 --> 01:10:06.691
Oh. l-l trust you.

1308
01:10:06.795 --> 01:10:11.404
l do trust you. l just want you
to tell me the truth.

1309
01:10:12.504 --> 01:10:15.073
Well. l did.

1310
01:10:15.178 --> 01:10:18.014
Well. then.
that's the end of it.

1311
01:10:29.313 --> 01:10:31.716
You would tell me.
wouldn't you?

1312
01:10:31.820 --> 01:10:32.863
Walter.

1313
01:10:32.967 --> 01:10:34.723
l just want you to
be honest with me.

1314
01:10:34.828 --> 01:10:37.664
l can take anything except lies.

1315
01:10:38.030 --> 01:10:40.433
People slip up.
Christ. l understand that.

1316
01:10:40.537 --> 01:10:42.436
lt happens all the time.

1317
01:10:42.540 --> 01:10:46.434
l mean. l'm not some meathead
chauvinist provincial.

1318
01:10:46.538 --> 01:10:48.442
ls that all?
- No. No.

1319
01:10:48.546 --> 01:10:51.615
l'm jealous.
l'm very jealous of Max.

1320
01:10:51.719 --> 01:10:54.267
l'm not crazy about the idea
of you sleeping with him. but if...

1321
01:10:54.371 --> 01:10:55.610
you did it and didn't tell me...

1322
01:10:55.714 --> 01:10:57.951
that would really bother me.

1323
01:10:58.055 --> 01:11:00.997
Without changing my plea.
l would like to know why.

1324
01:11:01.102 --> 01:11:03.331
Because it underestimates me.

1325
01:11:03.435 --> 01:11:05.389
Not telling me assumes
l'm incapable...

1326
01:11:05.494 --> 01:11:07.088
of understanding why you did it.

1327
01:11:07.192 --> 01:11:10.713
Not that you did it.
Had you done it.

1328
01:11:10.818 --> 01:11:12.716
Did you?

1329
01:11:12.821 --> 01:11:16.389
You want me to tell you the truth.
no matter how much it hurts.

1330
01:11:16.493 --> 01:11:18.646
lf we can't be honest
with each other.

1331
01:11:18.751 --> 01:11:19.976
what else have we got?

1332
01:11:20.080 --> 01:11:22.980
And you'll believe in me?
You'll understand?

1333
01:11:23.084 --> 01:11:25.983
Of course l will.
l love you.

1334
01:11:26.087 --> 01:11:31.234
l love you too. but l did not sleep
with Max last night.

1335
01:11:31.338 --> 01:11:33.237
No?

1336
01:11:33.341 --> 01:11:36.243
Can we knock this off
and go to sleep?

1337
01:11:36.347 --> 01:11:38.242
l love you.

1338
01:11:38.346 --> 01:11:40.432
Mmm.
l love you.

1339
01:11:40.432 --> 01:11:42.517
[ Click ]...

1340
01:11:46.890 --> 01:11:48.794
[ Click ]
- Walter?

1341
01:11:48.899 --> 01:11:51.718
Walter!
- [ Mutters ] Walter.

1342
01:11:51.822 --> 01:11:54.299
Are you awake?
- Yeah!

1343
01:11:54.403 --> 01:11:56.302
Yeah. l'm awake.
What is it?

1344
01:11:56.406 --> 01:11:58.304
l have to talk to you.

1345
01:11:58.408 --> 01:12:01.310
Oh. l can't believe
l'm gonna do this. lt's so stupid.

1346
01:12:01.414 --> 01:12:03.984
What is it?
What's the matter?

1347
01:12:04.616 --> 01:12:07.020
l lied to you about Max.

1348
01:12:07.124 --> 01:12:10.526
Apparently l went
to his apartment. l got drunk...

1349
01:12:10.631 --> 01:12:12.654
l guess l sang a few songs...

1350
01:12:12.758 --> 01:12:16.030
and apparently l. um...

1351
01:12:16.134 --> 01:12:18.032
slept with him.

1352
01:12:18.136 --> 01:12:20.390
l know l shouldn't
be telling you this.

1353
01:12:20.495 --> 01:12:21.537
No. No.

1354
01:12:21.642 --> 01:12:23.870
lt's okay.

1355
01:12:23.974 --> 01:12:27.697
lt's only proved to me
how much l love you.

1356
01:12:28.348 --> 01:12:31.590
Oh. that sounds stupid too.
but it's true.

1357
01:12:31.694 --> 01:12:33.589
l love you. Walter.
l love you.

1358
01:12:33.693 --> 01:12:36.090
l love you.
lt's okay.

1359
01:12:36.195 --> 01:12:38.094
Everything's okay.

1360
01:12:38.198 --> 01:12:41.100
You won't hold it against me?
You can forgive me?

1361
01:12:41.204 --> 01:12:44.103
Sure. Can we talk about this
in the morning?

1362
01:12:44.207 --> 01:12:46.102
l'm so tired.

1363
01:12:46.206 --> 01:12:49.230
Do we have to talk about it?
Can't we just put this behind us?

1364
01:12:49.334 --> 01:12:51.731
Yeah.

1365
01:12:51.835 --> 01:12:53.734
[ Chuckles ]...

1366
01:12:53.838 --> 01:12:55.736
l love you.

1367
01:12:55.840 --> 01:12:58.238
l love you.
[ Kissing Sound ]...

1368
01:12:58.342 --> 01:13:00.427
[ Sighs ]...

1369
01:13:00.472 --> 01:13:02.558
[ Click ]...

1370
01:13:05.594 --> 01:13:08.253
[ Click ]
- [ Walter ] You whore!

1371
01:13:08.357 --> 01:13:10.254
l leave town for 5
minutes. you can't...

1372
01:13:10.358 --> 01:13:12.254
wait to leap into the
sack with old Max!

1373
01:13:12.358 --> 01:13:14.255
You... bastard!

1374
01:13:14.359 --> 01:13:16.756
That's right! Laying it off on me!
- You hypocrite!

1375
01:13:16.860 --> 01:13:20.097
l'm not the one screwing around!
- ''Just be honest with me.''

1376
01:13:20.201 --> 01:13:24.676
How long has this been going on?
- You chauvinist meathead!

1377
01:13:24.780 --> 01:13:27.977
l'm not telling you anything!

1378
01:13:28.081 --> 01:13:29.979
Now or ever again!

1379
01:13:30.083 --> 01:13:32.017
Oh. this is perfect!
Guess who suddenly...

1380
01:13:32.122 --> 01:13:33.441
turns into the injured party!

1381
01:13:33.545 --> 01:13:36.447
Where do you think you're going?
- Someplace where you're not!

1382
01:13:36.551 --> 01:13:39.258
Well. then. you stay here.
because l'm leaving!

1383
01:13:39.362 --> 01:13:39.607
Fine!

1384
01:13:39.711 --> 01:13:42.620
Get out! l never want
to see you again!

1385
01:13:42.724 --> 01:13:44.809
[ Splat ]

1386
01:13:51.598 --> 01:13:54.433
The plasterer came?

1387
01:13:54.726 --> 01:13:57.424
? [ Radio.''La Bamba'']...

1388
01:13:57.528 --> 01:13:59.802
??

1389
01:13:59.907 --> 01:14:03.012
? Para bailar la bamba?

1390
01:14:03.116 --> 01:14:07.017
? Para bailar la bamba
se necesita?

1391
01:14:07.121 --> 01:14:09.479
? Una poca de gracia?
- [ Loud Rattling ]...

1392
01:14:09.583 --> 01:14:13.271
? Una poca de gracia
par mi para ti?

1393
01:14:13.375 --> 01:14:15.946
? [ Continues ]
- Hey. Walter.

1394
01:14:17.207 --> 01:14:20.115
What happened?
Your old lady kick you out?

1395
01:14:20.220 --> 01:14:21.517
l do not wish to discuss...

1396
01:14:21.621 --> 01:14:23.618
my domestic difficulties
with you. Julio.

1397
01:14:23.722 --> 01:14:26.872
That's okay. l figure she
threw his ass out.

1398
01:14:26.976 --> 01:14:30.663
No. she did not throw my ass out!
- No. you had your chance. man.

1399
01:14:30.768 --> 01:14:32.711
This is between me and Duke.

1400
01:14:32.816 --> 01:14:35.493
l'm not payin' you
guys to stand around.

1401
01:14:35.598 --> 01:14:37.047
You wanna get to work?

1402
01:14:37.151 --> 01:14:38.038
We can't do nothin'...

1403
01:14:38.143 --> 01:14:39.713
till the plumbin'
inspector gets here.

1404
01:14:39.817 --> 01:14:42.133
There's no plumbing in that wall.

1405
01:14:42.237 --> 01:14:44.400
No?
- We can take off and you can...

1406
01:14:44.504 --> 01:14:46.174
call us when he gets here.

1407
01:14:46.278 --> 01:14:50.798
Just stay where you are.
l fell for that one before.

1408
01:14:50.824 --> 01:14:53.022
Ooh! Ohh!
[ Sighs ]...

1409
01:14:53.126 --> 01:14:55.443
? [ Continues ]

1410
01:14:57.956 --> 01:15:00.360
You're up bright and early.

1411
01:15:00.464 --> 01:15:02.680
l didn't sleep very well.

1412
01:15:03.795 --> 01:15:05.699
You look great.
Got a date?

1413
01:15:05.804 --> 01:15:07.701
Yes.
with the Marine Corps Band.

1414
01:15:07.806 --> 01:15:09.546
l'm starting with the brass. and l'm...

1415
01:15:09.650 --> 01:15:11.207
working my way to
the drum section.

1416
01:15:11.311 --> 01:15:14.000
Don't you think we should talk?
- This is not the time.

1417
01:15:14.105 --> 01:15:17.006
l'm mad. and l'm getting madder.
- Oh! What do you think l am?

1418
01:15:17.110 --> 01:15:19.004
l think you're a jerk.
- l know that.

1419
01:15:19.109 --> 01:15:22.314
l didn't realize how big a jerk
l was until last night.

1420
01:15:22.418 --> 01:15:23.211
Neither did l.

1421
01:15:23.315 --> 01:15:25.340
Let's just pack it in. then. Let's just...

1422
01:15:25.444 --> 01:15:27.222
finish this thing
right here and now!

1423
01:15:27.326 --> 01:15:29.215
Fine.
- l'll pack a bag for you...

1424
01:15:29.319 --> 01:15:30.885
and send the rest later.

1425
01:15:30.989 --> 01:15:33.504
You expect me to move out?
- You shouldn't have...

1426
01:15:33.609 --> 01:15:34.889
any trouble finding a bed.

1427
01:15:34.993 --> 01:15:37.067
l got a bed. lady.
- Get the hell outta here!

1428
01:15:37.172 --> 01:15:37.892
This is private!

1429
01:15:37.996 --> 01:15:39.331
What makes you think you can...

1430
01:15:39.435 --> 01:15:40.904
just throw me out
of my own house?

1431
01:15:41.009 --> 01:15:42.903
You're the one who's moving.

1432
01:15:43.008 --> 01:15:45.045
l have worked and
slaved-- suffered...

1433
01:15:45.149 --> 01:15:47.242
and put myself in
hock up to my eyes...

1434
01:15:47.346 --> 01:15:48.576
and you want me to move out...

1435
01:15:48.680 --> 01:15:50.165
because you've got
the hots for Max?

1436
01:15:50.269 --> 01:15:52.163
No way!
You hear me?

1437
01:15:52.267 --> 01:15:54.579
l have worked and slaved
and suffered for...

1438
01:15:54.683 --> 01:15:56.834
this house every bit
as much as you have!

1439
01:15:56.938 --> 01:15:59.840
Actually more. because
l had to put up with you!

1440
01:15:59.944 --> 01:16:02.843
This is ridiculous!
You don't even like this house!

1441
01:16:02.947 --> 01:16:04.842
l love this house!

1442
01:16:04.946 --> 01:16:07.848
You've done nothing but complain
about it since we got here!

1443
01:16:07.952 --> 01:16:09.824
l did one other thing-- l sunk every...

1444
01:16:09.928 --> 01:16:11.850
nickel l had in the
world in this house!

1445
01:16:11.954 --> 01:16:13.687
And you'll get it all back!

1446
01:16:13.792 --> 01:16:15.854
Me and everyone you've ever met!

1447
01:16:15.958 --> 01:16:18.859
''l'll pay you back''
will be written on your gravestone!

1448
01:16:18.963 --> 01:16:21.357
l wouldn't give lectures
on the value of promises!

1449
01:16:21.462 --> 01:16:24.056
Your word didn't do too well
on this last outing!

1450
01:16:24.160 --> 01:16:24.856
Yours is fine!

1451
01:16:24.960 --> 01:16:27.868
lt's certainly a lot better
than your cheque!

1452
01:16:27.972 --> 01:16:30.335
[ All Murmuring ]...

1453
01:16:31.884 --> 01:16:34.498
l'll get you your money back!

1454
01:16:34.602 --> 01:16:35.917
I don't want the money!

1455
01:16:36.021 --> 01:16:38.169
This is my house.
and I'm not moving!

1456
01:16:38.273 --> 01:16:41.173
lt's a big house!
We'll divide it up!

1457
01:16:41.277 --> 01:16:44.969
You stay in your half.
l'll stay in mine!

1458
01:16:46.732 --> 01:16:49.513
That is such a dumb idea.

1459
01:16:49.617 --> 01:16:52.518
Sometimes it amazes me
you ever passed the bar.

1460
01:16:52.622 --> 01:16:54.004
l'm sure it does.

1461
01:16:54.108 --> 01:16:57.347
You've never passed
a bar in your life.

1462
01:16:57.451 --> 01:17:00.277
You are so much less attractive
when l'm sober.

1463
01:17:00.381 --> 01:17:04.195
Thank goodness it's not that often.
- All right. that's it!

1464
01:17:04.299 --> 01:17:07.449
l've had it with you. the house.
Max. the orchestra and everything!

1465
01:17:07.554 --> 01:17:10.452
How long will it take
to put this place together?

1466
01:17:10.557 --> 01:17:12.618
Two weeks.
- [ Workers Laughing ]...

1467
01:17:12.722 --> 01:17:14.665
[ Man Laughing ]
Two weeks! Two weeks.

1468
01:17:14.769 --> 01:17:19.000
Okay. we'll stick it out
until the house is finished.

1469
01:17:19.105 --> 01:17:21.336
Then we'll sell it.
get our money back...

1470
01:17:21.440 --> 01:17:23.504
and get the hell away
from each other.

1471
01:17:23.608 --> 01:17:25.694
Fine.

1472
01:17:27.064 --> 01:17:28.968
Get back to work!

1473
01:17:29.072 --> 01:17:31.473
[ Murmuring. Chattering ]

1474
01:17:34.780 --> 01:17:36.865
Bam! Zoom!

1475
01:18:07.104 --> 01:18:09.511
[ Sobs ]...

1476
01:18:27.708 --> 01:18:30.828
[ Speaks French ]...

1477
01:18:32.129 --> 01:18:34.536
[ Speaking Vietnamese ]

1478
01:18:51.315 --> 01:18:53.219
What are you doing here?

1479
01:18:53.323 --> 01:18:55.720
You missed a rehearsal.
- That's right.

1480
01:18:55.824 --> 01:18:58.422
Did you tell Walter
what happened between us?

1481
01:18:58.526 --> 01:18:58.718
Yes.

1482
01:18:58.822 --> 01:19:01.391
And what did he say?

1483
01:19:01.496 --> 01:19:03.396
Walter and l are through.

1484
01:19:03.500 --> 01:19:06.063
l hate us both.
- You'll get over it.

1485
01:19:06.167 --> 01:19:08.649
You'll come back to me.
- No.

1486
01:19:08.671 --> 01:19:11.329
l'm just going away someplace.

1487
01:19:11.339 --> 01:19:14.243
You can't go anywhere.
We have performances.

1488
01:19:14.347 --> 01:19:16.502
You don't understand. l have to...

1489
01:19:16.607 --> 01:19:18.956
get away from here.
from both of you.

1490
01:19:19.060 --> 01:19:21.630
You are leaving the symphony?

1491
01:19:22.221 --> 01:19:24.125
What have l done?

1492
01:19:24.229 --> 01:19:27.131
Oh. it wasn't your fault.
lt was my fault.

1493
01:19:27.235 --> 01:19:29.320
l was weak.

1494
01:19:30.062 --> 01:19:31.966
No. you weren't.

1495
01:19:32.070 --> 01:19:33.968
What?

1496
01:19:34.072 --> 01:19:36.157
l made it up.

1497
01:19:37.027 --> 01:19:38.931
You made what up. Max?

1498
01:19:39.035 --> 01:19:41.311
You slept in the bedroom.
l slept in the living room.

1499
01:19:41.415 --> 01:19:43.310
Sex would have been a miracle.

1500
01:19:43.415 --> 01:19:45.500
Oh. Max!

1501
01:19:45.584 --> 01:19:48.151
l wanted you back.
and l truly thought...

1502
01:19:48.255 --> 01:19:50.311
l could make you happy this time.

1503
01:19:50.415 --> 01:19:52.819
Oh. Max.

1504
01:19:52.923 --> 01:19:55.238
Tell Walter the truth.

1505
01:19:55.342 --> 01:19:57.241
No.

1506
01:19:57.345 --> 01:20:00.247
He couldn't forgive me.
and l can't forgive him for that.

1507
01:20:00.351 --> 01:20:03.750
He's lost a wonderful woman.
and l know what that's like.

1508
01:20:03.854 --> 01:20:05.750
l've lost many.

1509
01:20:05.854 --> 01:20:08.417
You must hate me.
- No.

1510
01:20:08.521 --> 01:20:12.591
l used to hate you.
Now l hate Walter.

1511
01:20:12.695 --> 01:20:14.841
Lucky guy.

1512
01:20:14.945 --> 01:20:17.305
[ Workers Chattering ]...

1513
01:20:17.409 --> 01:20:18.452
Walter!

1514
01:20:18.556 --> 01:20:20.309
Well. this is an
unexpected revulsion.

1515
01:20:20.413 --> 01:20:23.338
Are you hot?
Can l take your life?

1516
01:20:23.416 --> 01:20:25.311
l can see that my presence here...

1517
01:20:25.415 --> 01:20:27.313
could be construed
as in poor taste.

1518
01:20:27.417 --> 01:20:29.315
No!
- Do you realize what you've done?

1519
01:20:29.419 --> 01:20:31.861
You've taken
a woman who loves you...

1520
01:20:31.965 --> 01:20:34.865
one of the great women
on the face of this Earth...

1521
01:20:34.969 --> 01:20:36.864
and thrown her away.

1522
01:20:36.968 --> 01:20:38.964
l've lost her too. but l'll get over it...

1523
01:20:39.068 --> 01:20:40.869
because l am shallow
and self-centred.

1524
01:20:40.973 --> 01:20:44.696
But you. you won't
because you are complex.

1525
01:20:44.767 --> 01:20:49.537
You will suffer terrible anguish
for the rest of your life.

1526
01:20:49.641 --> 01:20:53.049
This is turning out to be
a pretty good day.

1527
01:20:53.153 --> 01:20:56.053
Good day.
- ?? [ Whistling ]

1528
01:20:56.157 --> 01:20:58.845
Smooth strokes.

1529
01:20:58.950 --> 01:21:01.096
Up and down.

1530
01:21:01.200 --> 01:21:04.392
Paint.
don't tickle.

1531
01:21:04.496 --> 01:21:06.581
And don't smoke.

1532
01:21:07.993 --> 01:21:10.449
? [ Whistling Continues ]

1533
01:21:52.955 --> 01:21:56.030
Well. folks. l guess this is
hasta ''so-long-a.''

1534
01:21:56.134 --> 01:21:58.028
[ Chuckles ]

1535
01:21:58.133 --> 01:22:00.030
You know.
just between us...

1536
01:22:00.135 --> 01:22:02.689
there were a couple of times
when l didn't think we'd ever be...

1537
01:22:02.794 --> 01:22:04.028
able to put this baby back up.

1538
01:22:04.132 --> 01:22:07.041
But it. uh. it turned out.
- lt's beautiful. Curly.

1539
01:22:07.145 --> 01:22:10.294
lt is. really. much better
than l imagined.

1540
01:22:10.398 --> 01:22:12.792
Thank you.
That's very nice of you.

1541
01:22:12.896 --> 01:22:15.422
One more job. though.
Here's your key.

1542
01:22:15.526 --> 01:22:19.071
lt's the only one l've got.
Who wants it?

1543
01:22:20.607 --> 01:22:22.693
Hmm?

1544
01:22:25.279 --> 01:22:29.186
Well. l'll just put it
on the bannister here.

1545
01:22:29.290 --> 01:22:32.191
You'll have no trouble
selling this place. that's for sure.

1546
01:22:32.295 --> 01:22:35.673
Shirk Brothers'll give you
a million for it tomorrow.

1547
01:22:35.778 --> 01:22:36.144
Great.

1548
01:22:36.248 --> 01:22:38.869
No. this wasn't an
easy one. but the...

1549
01:22:38.974 --> 01:22:41.321
foundation was good. l'll say that.

1550
01:22:41.425 --> 01:22:46.122
And if that's okay.
then everything else can be fixed.

1551
01:22:47.342 --> 01:22:50.090
Well. goodbye. folks.
Good luck.

1552
01:22:51.680 --> 01:22:54.136
[ Door Opens. Closes ]

1553
01:23:15.954 --> 01:23:18.040
Well. this is it.

1554
01:23:18.129 --> 01:23:21.820
Are you going
to spend the night here?

1555
01:23:21.924 --> 01:23:24.836
No. You?

1556
01:23:25.923 --> 01:23:28.008
l'm already packed.

1557
01:23:29.301 --> 01:23:31.871
l'd better get packed myself.

1558
01:23:32.304 --> 01:23:34.510
l'll get my bags.

1559
01:23:43.482 --> 01:23:45.567
Walter?

1560
01:23:46.819 --> 01:23:48.723
Walter?

1561
01:23:48.827 --> 01:23:51.685
This step.
This-- This was our step.

1562
01:23:51.789 --> 01:23:55.024
This is where it all started to--

1563
01:23:55.128 --> 01:23:57.022
Turn to crap.

1564
01:23:57.127 --> 01:23:59.024
[ Sighs ]

1565
01:23:59.129 --> 01:24:02.851
Too late to put it
back together. isn't it?

1566
01:24:10.133 --> 01:24:13.668
You slept with Max.
and l don't care.

1567
01:24:14.972 --> 01:24:17.375
What?

1568
01:24:17.479 --> 01:24:19.378
l don't care.

1569
01:24:19.482 --> 01:24:23.648
Well. l care. but not enough
for us to be apart.

1570
01:24:24.356 --> 01:24:26.093
Really?

1571
01:24:26.197 --> 01:24:28.095
Really.

1572
01:24:28.199 --> 01:24:30.326
l'm glad you slept with
him. because now...

1573
01:24:30.430 --> 01:24:32.100
l know how much l really love you.

1574
01:24:32.205 --> 01:24:34.283
You sleeping with Max
was the best thing...

1575
01:24:34.387 --> 01:24:35.772
that could've happened to us.

1576
01:24:35.876 --> 01:24:38.240
l didn't sleep with him.

1577
01:24:39.663 --> 01:24:41.748
Thank God.

1578
01:24:46.503 --> 01:24:52.120
? [''Ode to Joy'']...

1579
01:24:52.225 --> 01:24:57.667
??

1580
01:24:57.772 --> 01:25:02.505
? [ Singing In German ]...

1581
01:25:02.609 --> 01:25:06.638
[ Continues ]
- [ Shouting. Laughing ]...

1582
01:25:06.742 --> 01:25:09.596
??

1583
01:25:09.700 --> 01:25:11.680
Ohh!
- [ Man ] Over here!

1584
01:25:11.785 --> 01:25:15.686
Always a bridesmaid.
never a bride.

1585
01:25:15.790 --> 01:25:21.527
??

1586
